WEBVTT

00:01.069 --> 00:04.038
(piano playing
"As Time Goes By")

00:04.038 --> 00:06.707
(orchestra joins in,
music swells)

00:09.377 --> 00:12.480
(song concludes
with a flourish)

00:13.981 --> 00:17.185
(eerie tones playing)

00:28.496 --> 00:30.698
(low, ominous tone plays)

00:36.204 --> 00:38.772
(thunder rumbling)

00:38.772 --> 00:42.176
(acoustic guitar playing
upbeat intro)

00:44.678 --> 00:46.947
(thunder crashes)

00:46.947 --> 00:49.617
(horse neighs)

00:49.617 --> 00:52.120
(wind whistles)

00:53.254 --> 00:56.257
(waterfall rumbling,
stream flowing)

00:56.257 --> 00:59.560
(branch creaking)

00:59.560 --> 01:02.230
* *

01:05.733 --> 01:08.402
(car engine revving)

01:15.543 --> 01:18.346
* *

01:19.147 --> 01:20.481
(sneezes)

01:20.481 --> 01:22.483
(church bell tolling)

01:26.587 --> 01:27.955
(doors creak)

01:27.955 --> 01:28.922
Who are you?!

01:28.922 --> 01:30.090
(chuckles)

01:30.090 --> 01:31.792
Hello. I'm Nancy Drew.

01:31.792 --> 01:33.194
It's nice to meet you.

01:33.194 --> 01:35.396
May I ask who you are?

01:36.430 --> 01:37.998
Guess.

01:37.998 --> 01:39.500
All right.
I'm guessing you two

01:39.500 --> 01:41.101
are working
with Lawrence McNabb,

01:41.101 --> 01:42.970
the locksmith,
that he gives you the keys

01:42.970 --> 01:45.639
and you're responsible for
the recent string of burglaries.

01:45.639 --> 01:46.707
However,

01:46.707 --> 01:48.609
you should know
the DA's only interested

01:48.609 --> 01:51.279
in McNabb-- you two
could make a deal with him.

01:51.279 --> 01:52.846
And that
Charlie the security guard

01:52.846 --> 01:55.816
is about to walk
through that door.

01:55.816 --> 01:58.152
(door creaks open)

01:58.152 --> 02:00.954
(door creaking closed)
(meekly): Hi.

02:00.954 --> 02:04.158
(sirens wailing)

02:08.596 --> 02:10.431
Listen to me.
I'll get Pastor Murray

02:10.431 --> 02:11.765
to drop the
breaking-and-entering charges

02:11.765 --> 02:13.767
if you agree
to some kind of counseling.

02:13.767 --> 02:15.703
(sighs):
Anger issues don't just go away.

02:15.703 --> 02:18.772
I don't need a shrink!
(whispers): Yeah, you do.

02:18.772 --> 02:20.741
He gets cranky
when he hasn't eaten.

02:20.741 --> 02:22.576
I told him, you know,
go have a snack.

02:22.576 --> 02:26.280
I said, "Before we get here,
you better have a snack."

02:26.280 --> 02:28.349
Oh, one summer,
we were on Fire Island...

02:28.349 --> 02:30.318
Hey! Psst!
Not with that story again!

02:30.318 --> 02:31.819
(sirens wail in distance)

02:31.819 --> 02:34.188
Hold on.

02:34.188 --> 02:35.356
What's that?

02:35.356 --> 02:37.024
My sleuth kit.

02:37.024 --> 02:38.459
Flashlight,

02:38.459 --> 02:39.760
fountain pen, notebook,

02:39.760 --> 02:42.162
magnifying glass,
fingerprint powder,

02:42.162 --> 02:44.632
digital recorder and...

02:47.901 --> 02:50.271
...one of Hannah's lemon bars.

02:52.139 --> 02:54.408
(tires screech, siren stops)

02:54.408 --> 02:57.811
(garbled police radio
transmissions)

02:57.811 --> 02:59.613
Bess, is Nancy okay?

02:59.613 --> 03:01.482
Are you kidding?
She's loving it.

03:01.482 --> 03:03.951
Okay, here he is.
Nancy?

03:03.951 --> 03:05.486
(laughs):
Hi, Ned.

03:05.486 --> 03:07.321
So, I had this dream
during my nap today

03:07.321 --> 03:08.589
where you went off to California

03:08.589 --> 03:09.990
and met that guy on Smallville,

03:09.990 --> 03:12.860
and you got amnesia and...

03:12.860 --> 03:14.462
literally forgot
you ever met me,

03:14.462 --> 03:16.297
and then I turned
into a squirrel.

03:16.297 --> 03:18.766
Anyway, what do you think
that means?

03:18.766 --> 03:21.502
(groans): Um, Ned, can we
talk about this later?

03:21.502 --> 03:23.437
I'm just a little busy.

03:23.437 --> 03:24.972
Yeah, sorry.

03:24.972 --> 03:25.973
O-Okay.

03:25.973 --> 03:27.241
Not appropriate, Ned.

03:27.241 --> 03:29.410
You take naps?

03:29.410 --> 03:31.011
What's going on?
Is she okay?

03:31.011 --> 03:33.781
Hey, now, don't worry,
I just talked with her--

03:33.781 --> 03:34.648
she's doing fine.

03:34.648 --> 03:36.183
That Nancy's my best man.

03:36.183 --> 03:37.585
I-I mean,

03:37.585 --> 03:40.588
she would be if she
were on the force.

03:43.757 --> 03:46.059
Fine. Therapy.

03:46.059 --> 03:48.296
Great. I'll call
the D.A. back.

03:48.296 --> 03:49.830
(laughs)

03:51.399 --> 03:54.968
(sighs): I just want
to thank you, Nancy Drew.

03:54.968 --> 03:57.605
I've always heard the
nicest things about you,

03:57.605 --> 03:59.873
the way you solve mysteries
and you help people...

03:59.873 --> 04:01.008
Steve...

04:01.008 --> 04:03.010
please don't thank her
for turning us in.

04:03.010 --> 04:06.046
I think Crankenstein needs
another lemon bar.

04:06.046 --> 04:10.551
Well, I thought the
Crankosaurus was extinct.

04:10.551 --> 04:12.686
I don't know about this.
Well, I'm sorry,

04:12.686 --> 04:15.756
Cranky Doodle Dandy.
(laughs)

04:15.756 --> 04:17.491
I can't do this.

04:17.491 --> 04:19.026
Gary, we made a deal.

04:19.026 --> 04:20.728
The deal's gone wrong.

04:20.728 --> 04:23.163
Hey, where is she?
We need her!

04:23.163 --> 04:25.566
You take that side.

04:25.566 --> 04:28.001
(ominous, jazzy theme plays)

04:31.805 --> 04:33.607
(low scratching)

04:40.448 --> 04:42.483
* *

04:42.483 --> 04:44.885
(quiet grunting)

04:44.885 --> 04:46.820
Hey, Gary, look.

04:47.655 --> 04:52.893
Hey! Let's get out of here.

04:52.893 --> 04:53.961
It's Nancy!

04:53.961 --> 04:56.630
(excited chatter)
WOMAN: It's Nancy!

04:59.299 --> 05:00.901
Hi, everybody.

05:03.537 --> 05:06.640
Hold it there!
Hold it right there!

05:10.110 --> 05:11.545
(gasps)

05:11.545 --> 05:14.582
(crowd gasps, woman screams)

05:14.582 --> 05:18.185
WOMAN:
Oh, my goodness!

05:18.185 --> 05:20.588
(crowd gasps)
MAN: Hold on!

05:20.588 --> 05:22.856
MAN:
Hold on to that gutter!

05:22.856 --> 05:24.958
YOUNG WOMAN:
Come on, Nancy, hold on tight!

05:24.958 --> 05:28.228
Hold on, Nancy--
we got the fire department here!

05:28.228 --> 05:30.998
That's all right, Chief--
I'll be down in a jiffy.

05:30.998 --> 05:33.734
Hang on, Nancy!

05:42.376 --> 05:46.213
* *

05:46.213 --> 05:48.882
(people cheering))

05:48.882 --> 05:50.751
(laughing)

05:50.751 --> 05:53.921
Yay!
Yay, Nancy!

05:53.921 --> 05:55.523
Are you okay?

05:55.523 --> 05:56.757
I'm fine, Dad.

05:56.757 --> 05:58.091
Really, in the
sleuthing business,

05:58.091 --> 05:59.793
this kind of thing
happens all the time.

05:59.793 --> 06:01.529
It really isn't
a big deal.

06:01.529 --> 06:04.064
It is a big deal.

06:04.064 --> 06:05.699
I ran from the courthouse

06:05.699 --> 06:07.968
in the middle
of that eviction case,

06:07.968 --> 06:10.270
which the judge, he...

06:10.270 --> 06:12.339
he didn't appreciate.

06:12.339 --> 06:13.641
Where is your car?

06:13.641 --> 06:17.077
Around the corner.
(sighs)

06:18.278 --> 06:19.480
(sighs)

06:19.480 --> 06:21.515
Is now a better time?

06:21.515 --> 06:23.717
'Cause I wanted
to give you this.

06:23.717 --> 06:25.719
Wha...
You know, your hunch

06:25.719 --> 06:27.755
was right on
the nose, Nancy.

06:27.755 --> 06:31.191
Just wish you could've clued
us in a little earlier.

06:31.191 --> 06:32.426
Nancy! Nancy!
Thank God!

06:32.426 --> 06:33.461
Nancy, right here.

06:33.461 --> 06:34.828
Hi, Nancy.

06:34.828 --> 06:37.397
(laughter)
Smile!

06:37.397 --> 06:38.732
Thank you.
Bye.

06:38.732 --> 06:41.034
Nancy, what are we
gonna do without you?

06:41.034 --> 06:43.504
It's only for a few
months-- I'll be back.

06:43.504 --> 06:44.638
The image of
your mother.

06:44.638 --> 06:45.773
Do you remember
her at all?

06:45.773 --> 06:48.742
No.
She was such a lovely woman,

06:48.742 --> 06:51.579
so kind and intelligent.

06:51.579 --> 06:54.114
Just like you, Nancy.

06:55.549 --> 06:56.817
(honks horn twice)

06:56.817 --> 06:58.519
Bye, everybody.
Bye-bye.

06:58.519 --> 06:59.853
So long, Nancy!

07:05.058 --> 07:08.862
Shall we all pray for her
safe journey to California?

07:08.862 --> 07:09.997
Sure.

07:09.997 --> 07:13.000
Dear Lord, please
watch over Nancy Drew

07:13.000 --> 07:16.770
and protect her as she
strives to solve mysteries

07:16.770 --> 07:21.509
that are beyond the abilities of
local law enforcement agencies.

07:21.509 --> 07:23.877
(birds chirping)

07:23.877 --> 07:25.078
(sighs)

07:25.078 --> 07:27.314
Dad, I...
I want you to promise--

07:27.314 --> 07:29.717
no more sleuthing, at least
while we're in California.

07:29.717 --> 07:32.786
You go to school,
shopping,

07:32.786 --> 07:34.254
spend some time
with teenagers.

07:34.254 --> 07:36.256
It's what you're
supposed to be doing.

07:36.256 --> 07:38.458
Give it a try.

07:39.326 --> 07:41.529
(birds chirping)

07:43.363 --> 07:45.165
(turns engine off)

07:45.165 --> 07:47.501
You know, I've always picked
cases that help people.

07:47.501 --> 07:49.336
"Others first."
That's right.

07:49.336 --> 07:51.639
But this one... this
is a little different.

07:51.639 --> 07:53.006
If everything goes well,

07:53.006 --> 07:55.676
I could start making
some... real money.

07:55.676 --> 07:57.845
We have enough money, Dad.
Well, I'll be the judge

07:57.845 --> 07:59.479
of that, thank you.
At any rate,

07:59.479 --> 08:03.250
I'm starting something new--
I-I can't be worried about...

08:03.250 --> 08:05.819
(phone rings, Dad groans)

08:07.387 --> 08:09.222
How you doing, John?

08:09.222 --> 08:11.491
Yeah, I'll meet you
at the deposition

08:11.491 --> 08:13.594
as soon as my
train gets in.

08:13.594 --> 08:14.795
(Nancy sighs)

08:14.795 --> 08:16.429
Well, we don't have
an airport out here.

08:16.429 --> 08:17.765
I wish I was kidding.

08:17.765 --> 08:20.634
This is a terrible
development!

08:20.634 --> 08:22.002
What are you gonna do?

08:22.002 --> 08:24.572
You have a mystery to
solve in La-La Land.

08:24.572 --> 08:26.874
I'll figure something out.

08:26.874 --> 08:28.208
(sighs)

08:28.208 --> 08:29.877
I hope.

08:33.413 --> 08:35.849
Ned!

08:35.849 --> 08:40.520
With all the commotion,
I didn't get to give you this.

08:43.323 --> 08:45.325
I needed a new compass.

08:45.325 --> 08:47.227
The old one's wobbly.

08:47.227 --> 08:48.696
Thank you.

08:48.696 --> 08:51.031
In case I'm not with
you on your birthday.

08:51.031 --> 08:52.966
That's so sweet.

08:52.966 --> 08:56.436
I just don't know
if I'll get to use it.

08:56.436 --> 08:58.572
Why?
Well, my dad

08:58.572 --> 09:01.141
let me choose the house
we're gonna live in,

09:01.141 --> 09:02.342
so I chose one with...

09:02.342 --> 09:04.578
With a mystery.

09:04.578 --> 09:05.913
But not just any mystery.

09:05.913 --> 09:08.415
One of the greatest
unsolved cases of all time--

09:08.415 --> 09:09.850
Dehlia Draycott.

09:10.884 --> 09:13.153
The movie actress.
Mm-hmm?

09:13.153 --> 09:14.755
Before your time.

09:14.755 --> 09:15.856
25 years ago,

09:15.856 --> 09:19.026
at the height of her fame,

09:19.026 --> 09:21.762
she disappeared
for five months.

09:21.762 --> 09:24.064
Nobody knew where.

09:24.064 --> 09:27.935
And when she came back,
she threw a giant party.

09:27.935 --> 09:32.272
But she never went downstairs
to greet her guests.

09:32.272 --> 09:37.444
She was found floating
in the pool... dead.

09:37.444 --> 09:39.112
Gee, that sounds
like fun.

09:39.112 --> 09:42.049
I know, right? But I didn't
tell my dad about the house,

09:42.049 --> 09:44.151
and now he's not letting me
do any sleuthing.

09:44.151 --> 09:45.986
I mean, there was
a hostage situation,

09:45.986 --> 09:48.455
so I can kind of see
his point, but, um...

09:48.455 --> 09:50.123
DAD:
Hi, Ned. Bye, Ned.

09:50.123 --> 09:51.491
Got to scoot, Nancy.

09:51.491 --> 09:52.693
Mr. Drew!

09:52.693 --> 09:55.195
Some Pfeffernusse, just in case.
Oh.

09:55.195 --> 09:57.264
And some ginger cupcakes--
your favorite.

09:57.264 --> 09:59.166
You're gonna get hungry
on the train...

09:59.166 --> 10:01.468
GIRL: Nancy! Nancy! Hold on!
Thank you so much.

10:01.468 --> 10:02.836
Bye, guys.
Nancy!

10:02.836 --> 10:04.872
(crying): Bye, Nancy.

10:04.872 --> 10:07.675
Now, you're gonna have
a safe train ride, okay?

10:07.675 --> 10:09.042
I'll miss you.
Don't get hurt.

10:09.042 --> 10:11.144
And please, you have
to keep us in contact.

10:11.144 --> 10:14.915
Um, Ned, don't worry about
that guy from Smallville.

10:14.915 --> 10:17.617
He's not my type.
DAD: Nancy?

10:18.418 --> 10:20.353
You have a type?

10:20.353 --> 10:22.589
(bright rock melody playing)

10:22.589 --> 10:24.191
Chief McGinnis!

10:24.191 --> 10:27.761
I just want to let you know that
I'm not sleuthing anymore. Bye!

10:28.628 --> 10:30.964
Nancy Drew not
sleuthing anymore?

10:30.964 --> 10:34.467
(chuckles):
I don't think so.

10:34.467 --> 10:38.171
(train whistle blows)

10:42.843 --> 10:44.812
* Come to California *

10:44.812 --> 10:48.682
* Baby, let it all hang out *

10:50.784 --> 10:52.786
* Come to California *

10:52.786 --> 10:56.156
* Tell us what it's all about *

10:57.958 --> 11:01.328
* But watch your mind
little bit, 'cause the future *

11:01.328 --> 11:03.330
* Is beginning *

11:03.330 --> 11:06.133
* Now, now *

11:06.133 --> 11:08.068
* Flew in to L.A. *

11:08.068 --> 11:11.204
* Caught a screening
of your lifelong dream *

11:11.204 --> 11:14.441
(man speaks indistinctly
over P.A. system)

11:14.441 --> 11:15.976
* Blew it in L.A. *

11:15.976 --> 11:19.847
* Now you're desperate
to create your own scene *

11:21.248 --> 11:23.550
Oh!
* Watch your mind little bit *

11:23.550 --> 11:27.087
* 'Cause you're headed
into the machine *

11:29.389 --> 11:30.758
* Come to California *

11:30.758 --> 11:32.726
* Come to California *

11:32.726 --> 11:34.627
* Come to California *

11:34.627 --> 11:36.696
* Come to California *

11:36.696 --> 11:38.866
* Come to California *

11:38.866 --> 11:40.868
* Never want to go away *

11:40.868 --> 11:42.602
* Come to California *

11:42.602 --> 11:44.938
* Come to California *

11:44.938 --> 11:47.574
* And watch your mind
little bit *

11:47.574 --> 11:49.810
* 'Cause you're headed
into the machine... *

11:51.511 --> 11:54.247
Hi. This is Carson Drew--
I'm running a little late.

11:54.247 --> 11:57.217
Hey, Dad, don't you think
people who talk on cell phones,

11:57.217 --> 11:58.451
uh, miss things?
Like what?

11:58.451 --> 12:00.353
Like that woman in the street.
(grunts)

12:00.353 --> 12:01.721
(tires screech)
WOMAN (laughs): Oh!

12:01.721 --> 12:03.791
(grunts)

12:03.791 --> 12:06.726
WOMAN:
Uh, uh, Mr. Drew? Nancy?

12:06.726 --> 12:08.261
Yes.

12:08.261 --> 12:11.031
(laughs): Hi. Thank you so much
for not running me over.

12:11.031 --> 12:13.901
I'm Barbara Barbara,
of Barbara Barbara Realty.

12:13.901 --> 12:15.969
You're here.

12:15.969 --> 12:18.505
Oh, I'm gonna get
right out of your way.

12:21.741 --> 12:24.744
(gates rattling)

12:30.784 --> 12:32.986
How do you love it?

12:38.491 --> 12:40.493
Oh! Gorgeous!

12:40.493 --> 12:41.929
(gasps)

12:41.929 --> 12:44.031
(door creaks)
Welcome.

12:50.270 --> 12:52.973
It's not exactly
what I had in mind,

12:52.973 --> 12:55.008
especially given the price.

12:55.008 --> 12:57.444
BARBARA (chuckles):
Well, as I told your daughter

12:57.444 --> 13:00.347
on the phone,
you do pay a premium for m...

13:00.347 --> 13:02.950
(closes piano)
Oh, I am such an oaf.

13:02.950 --> 13:06.086
Um, as you were saying,
you pay a premium for history,

13:06.086 --> 13:08.155
architectural significance.

13:08.155 --> 13:10.257
I mean, Dad,
look at this woodwork.

13:10.257 --> 13:12.926
Yeah, what-what she said.
Who's this?

13:12.926 --> 13:15.495
Dehlia Draycott,
the great film legend.

13:15.495 --> 13:16.763
This was her home.

13:16.763 --> 13:18.731
Didn't your
daughter tell you?

13:18.731 --> 13:22.870
We've, uh, both
been somewhat busy.

13:22.870 --> 13:25.605
(phone ringing)
Oh, excuse me.

13:25.605 --> 13:28.041
Yeah, hello?

13:28.708 --> 13:30.177
Do you know what?

13:30.177 --> 13:32.579
With a little tweaking,
you could be adorable.

13:32.579 --> 13:34.714
Um, thank you?

13:34.714 --> 13:36.950
Yes, you're just a makeover
waiting to happen.

13:36.950 --> 13:39.552
I'm gonna give you
the name of my stylist.

13:39.552 --> 13:42.555
Oh, come on, let's go
upstairs-- I can't wait

13:42.555 --> 13:44.691
to show you.

13:44.691 --> 13:47.227
Did you hear something?

13:49.129 --> 13:51.598
I suddenly got a chill.

13:54.201 --> 13:57.037
(brooding, mysterious
theme playing)

14:02.742 --> 14:06.013
Have a look around if you want.

14:09.382 --> 14:11.084
(gasps)

14:11.084 --> 14:13.120
Don't be afraid.

14:13.120 --> 14:16.223
Please, don't be afraid of me.

14:19.126 --> 14:21.161
I'm here to help you.

14:21.161 --> 14:24.831
You don't understand.
I want to... I want to help you.

14:24.831 --> 14:26.866
(frightened gasps)

14:26.866 --> 14:29.569
(laughing)

14:29.569 --> 14:31.671
I love that.

14:31.671 --> 14:34.774
They fall for it
every time.

14:34.774 --> 14:36.043
That's the projector.

14:36.043 --> 14:38.745
Oh, it's from one
of her old movies.

14:38.745 --> 14:41.381
There are so many booby traps
all over this house.

14:41.381 --> 14:44.484
People get so scared sometimes,
they wet their pants.

14:44.484 --> 14:45.485
(laughing)

14:45.485 --> 14:47.887
(chuckles):
Where's the gift shop?

14:47.887 --> 14:49.957
That's the spirit.

14:49.957 --> 14:51.925
Look, Miss Barbara Barbara,
I know I called

14:51.925 --> 14:53.826
asking for a house
with a mystery,

14:53.826 --> 14:55.862
but, um, things have changed,

14:55.862 --> 14:57.597
and... it's complicated,

14:57.597 --> 15:00.333
but... we're gonna need
a different house.

15:00.333 --> 15:03.370
Honey cheeks, read
the fine print:

15:03.370 --> 15:05.238
no refunds,
no exchanges.

15:05.238 --> 15:08.475
And besides, you know, there's
nothing else available...

15:08.475 --> 15:10.877
in your price range.

15:10.877 --> 15:13.680
(brief chuckle)

15:15.848 --> 15:17.017
I'm just gonna
use the gents,

15:17.017 --> 15:18.518
then I have to run
to that deposition.

15:18.518 --> 15:20.887
Watch this.
(ghostly shrieking)

15:20.887 --> 15:22.889
(Dad gasping, yelling)

15:22.889 --> 15:24.891
(panting)

15:24.891 --> 15:27.594
(laughing)

15:27.594 --> 15:29.229
Something just happened
in the bathroom

15:29.229 --> 15:32.132
which I am at a loss
to explain.

15:32.132 --> 15:34.701
(chuckles): The house
has a haunted theme.

15:34.701 --> 15:36.236
It's like a theme park.

15:36.236 --> 15:37.971
It's so fun, right, Dad?

15:37.971 --> 15:39.706
No.

15:41.608 --> 15:44.544
BARBARA: Oh, did I mention?
There's a strange caretaker.

15:44.544 --> 15:47.180
He lives in an apartment
down the hill.

15:47.180 --> 15:48.681
Uh, what's your name?

15:48.681 --> 15:51.384
Leshing. Let me know if there's
anything I can do for you.

15:51.384 --> 15:54.721
Nancy Drew.
Thank you very much.

15:54.721 --> 15:56.223
Uh, Leshing,

15:56.223 --> 15:59.726
we need to talk
about the lawn.

15:59.726 --> 16:02.329
* *

16:02.329 --> 16:04.964
(crickets chirping)

16:06.033 --> 16:08.968
(distant creaking echoes)

16:08.968 --> 16:11.004
Mm.

16:14.841 --> 16:17.444
Dad?

16:17.444 --> 16:19.312
M-Mr. Leshing?

16:19.312 --> 16:22.349
(distant creaking echoes)

16:23.883 --> 16:25.485
Hmm.

16:33.060 --> 16:34.727
(distant thud)

16:34.727 --> 16:37.730
(chandelier tinkling)

16:37.730 --> 16:39.766
(creaking)

16:41.201 --> 16:43.903
(distant thud)

16:43.903 --> 16:48.075
Someone stole my moccasins
and an important folder.

16:48.075 --> 16:50.277
Mysteries just find
you, don't they?

16:50.277 --> 16:53.213
I'm letting the professionals
handle this one.

16:53.213 --> 16:54.581
I'm on hold with the LAPD.

16:54.581 --> 16:58.585
Oh, calling the police
to solve a crime.

16:58.585 --> 16:59.986
I like it.

16:59.986 --> 17:01.488
It's been 57 minutes.

17:01.488 --> 17:04.191
They must be having
a busy night.

17:04.191 --> 17:06.693
(door creaks)

17:06.693 --> 17:10.130
(snoring)

17:10.130 --> 17:12.598
Yes. I'd like to
report a theft.

17:12.598 --> 17:14.101
I'm sorry!

17:14.101 --> 17:15.602
A favorite pair of
moccasin slippers

17:15.602 --> 17:17.470
and a Pee Chee folder
have been stolen.

17:17.470 --> 17:19.038
Please send an officer over
immediately.

17:19.038 --> 17:23.242
(man on phone laughing)

17:24.977 --> 17:26.512
(beep)

17:26.512 --> 17:29.216
Someone must have told a joke
over at the precinct.

17:29.216 --> 17:32.285
Yeah. That's it.

17:32.285 --> 17:34.121
Because it would be
irresponsible

17:34.121 --> 17:37.290
for a police department
to laugh at a crime.

17:38.625 --> 17:40.327
You're right.

17:40.327 --> 17:42.529
(quietly):
Yeah.

17:47.967 --> 17:50.002
(crickets chirping
outside)

17:50.002 --> 17:52.004
(distant creaking echoes)

17:52.004 --> 17:54.107
Dad?

18:02.449 --> 18:04.951
(phone rings in distance)

18:04.951 --> 18:06.386
Hello?
Leshing, this is Nancy.

18:06.386 --> 18:08.288
I needed to prove
your whereabouts.

18:08.288 --> 18:10.390
Go back to sleep.

18:11.558 --> 18:13.226
(door closes in distance)

18:13.226 --> 18:14.861
(distant footsteps)

18:25.472 --> 18:27.574
Someone's in the house.

18:27.574 --> 18:30.210
How did you get
here so quickly?

18:30.210 --> 18:31.711
If you're accusing me...

18:31.711 --> 18:32.945
(creaking)

18:32.945 --> 18:34.747
The attic.

18:42.822 --> 18:44.724
(creaking)

18:52.899 --> 18:54.867
(footsteps approaching)

18:56.068 --> 18:59.539
How is it possible for
someone to be in the attic

18:59.539 --> 19:02.141
and escape while we're
coming up the stairs?

19:02.141 --> 19:03.976
Is there another
staircase?

19:03.976 --> 19:06.346
No.

19:06.346 --> 19:08.715
Do you believe in ghosts,
Mr. Leshing?

19:08.715 --> 19:11.184
I am a ghost.

19:11.184 --> 19:12.385
(footsteps approaching)

19:12.385 --> 19:14.721
The Four Seasons
isn't haunted.

19:14.721 --> 19:16.122
What do you say?

19:16.122 --> 19:18.491
Dad, you hate hotels.

19:18.491 --> 19:20.927
Spa treatments...

19:20.927 --> 19:22.595
room service...

19:22.595 --> 19:25.832
These books
must have been Dehlia's.

19:25.832 --> 19:27.867
May I borrow some?

19:27.867 --> 19:29.001
If it were up to me,

19:29.001 --> 19:31.137
I wouldn't let anybody
in the house, period,

19:31.137 --> 19:32.372
but you're paying the rent,

19:32.372 --> 19:34.274
so do what you want.

19:34.274 --> 19:35.642
I'm sorry, I didn't mean...

19:35.642 --> 19:37.410
Good night.

19:43.683 --> 19:45.818
I like him.

19:45.818 --> 19:47.954
So...

19:47.954 --> 19:50.757
turns out there's
a mystery here after all.

19:50.757 --> 19:54.227
Dad, that mystery stuff
is so boring to me now.

19:54.227 --> 19:55.928
I've completely moved on.

19:55.928 --> 19:57.163
Mm-hmm.

19:57.163 --> 19:58.398
It was really
just a phase, you know,

19:58.398 --> 20:00.400
like papier-mache or puppets.

20:00.400 --> 20:03.236
It's over, done,
finished, gone forever.

20:03.236 --> 20:05.572
Got it.

20:09.276 --> 20:10.943
(sighs)

20:14.113 --> 20:16.182
WOMAN:
"Z... I'm sorry

20:16.182 --> 20:18.385
"to have vanished like I did.

20:18.385 --> 20:20.787
"I know you have been
looking for me.

20:20.787 --> 20:22.889
"Something important
happened last week.

20:22.889 --> 20:25.658
"I can't be the Dehlia
I was anymore.

20:25.658 --> 20:27.694
"I'm writing a new will.

20:27.694 --> 20:32.064
I need to make provisions
for someone else. D."

20:32.064 --> 20:35.335
D is Dehlia, but who's Z?

20:35.335 --> 20:37.704
Who's the someone else?

20:38.805 --> 20:40.006
No.

20:40.006 --> 20:41.641
I'm not sleuthing.

20:41.641 --> 20:43.075
(chuckles):
No, sirree.

20:43.075 --> 20:45.878
You're just reading a letter
that happens to be

20:45.878 --> 20:48.381
a major clue in
a fantastically famous mystery.

20:48.381 --> 20:50.483
But that means nothing to you.

20:50.483 --> 20:52.752
You're gonna go to bed
and be reasonable, Nancy.

20:52.752 --> 20:54.654
You're going
to a new school tomorrow.

20:54.654 --> 20:56.356
You're gonna make
wonderful friends.

20:56.356 --> 20:58.024
You're a normal teenager.

20:58.024 --> 20:59.859
You really are.

20:59.859 --> 21:01.694
Yeah.

21:04.196 --> 21:05.998
(exhales)

21:05.998 --> 21:08.935
(crickets chirping)

21:08.935 --> 21:10.370
(exhales)

21:10.370 --> 21:12.705
(birds chirping)

21:16.509 --> 21:19.211
(alarm rings)

21:19.211 --> 21:21.881
(pop intro plays)

