23:19.298 --> 23:21.734
(song fading out)

23:21.734 --> 23:24.136
* You're pretty much amazing *

23:24.136 --> 23:26.706
* Whoo-hoo *

23:26.706 --> 23:29.442
* You're pretty much
amazing... *

23:40.520 --> 23:42.188
Hi.

23:42.188 --> 23:43.222
Hello.

23:43.222 --> 23:44.724
Hi. Uh, I noticed

23:44.724 --> 23:46.559
you were wearing
penny loafers.

23:46.559 --> 23:47.860
Did your podiatrist

23:47.860 --> 23:49.896
suggest them,
or are you being ironic?

23:49.896 --> 23:51.564
I like old-fashioned things.

23:51.564 --> 23:53.566
Oh, we've noticed.

23:53.566 --> 23:56.135
Penny loafers are practical.

23:56.135 --> 23:57.403
Well,

23:57.403 --> 24:01.941
we may be on the brink of a
penny loafer fashion moment.

24:01.941 --> 24:04.477
Or not.

24:10.382 --> 24:12.819
(laughing)
That was awesome.

24:12.819 --> 24:16.556
Give that cupcake back.
Shut up!

24:16.556 --> 24:19.025
(laughing):
Come on.

24:20.059 --> 24:22.962
That's a good cupcake.

24:22.962 --> 24:24.531
NANCY: Principal Fineman,
I feel strongly,

24:24.531 --> 24:27.066
students should be given
a more nutritious alternative

24:27.066 --> 24:30.336
in the cafeteria--
perhaps a salad bar.

24:30.336 --> 24:33.506
A salad bar.
Terrific idea.

24:33.506 --> 24:34.741
Yeah. Hi.
I think the principal

24:34.741 --> 24:36.408
wants to yell at me
or something.

24:36.408 --> 24:37.710
Let's see.

24:37.710 --> 24:39.979
Oh, yes-- there may be
traces of lead paint

24:39.979 --> 24:42.114
in the utility shed
next to the volleyball courts.

24:42.114 --> 24:45.652
But I can't be certain until
the lab report comes back.

24:45.652 --> 24:47.053
Lead paint.

24:47.053 --> 24:48.320
That's bad, right?

24:48.320 --> 24:49.922
Very bad.

24:49.922 --> 24:52.158
But there's no
need to panic.

24:52.158 --> 24:56.162
Finally, I urge you
to offer a course in CPR.

24:56.162 --> 24:58.064
(both snicker)

24:58.064 --> 25:00.199
I noticed it wasn't part
of your curriculum.

25:00.199 --> 25:02.835
I'm certified, and I have
found great peace of mind

25:02.835 --> 25:04.871
knowing I may save
a life someday.

25:04.871 --> 25:08.708
(percussion playing,
cheerleaders shouting)

25:08.708 --> 25:11.644
CHEERLEADERS:
So hot! So hot! So hot...

25:11.644 --> 25:14.080
(cheering, whistling)

25:20.319 --> 25:22.722
(whooping)

25:27.694 --> 25:29.996
(cheering)

25:29.996 --> 25:33.365
(percussion continues,
cheerleaders continue)

25:33.365 --> 25:35.367
CHEERLEADERS: Ching, ching,
ching, ching, ching, ching!

25:35.367 --> 25:36.502
Where's the money?

25:36.502 --> 25:38.104
Cha-ching, where's the money?

25:44.343 --> 25:47.580
(coughing, choking)

25:48.615 --> 25:52.218
Corky! Corky!
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

25:52.218 --> 25:53.485
M-My brother's choking!

25:53.485 --> 25:54.854
(blows whistle)

25:54.854 --> 25:56.088
My brother's choking!
Time-out! Time-out!

25:56.088 --> 25:58.357
