Does anyone know CPR?

25:58.357 --> 25:59.926
Does anyone know CPR?

25:59.926 --> 26:01.761
NANCY:
I do. I know CPR.

26:01.761 --> 26:05.865
Excuse me.

26:05.865 --> 26:08.300
(Corky coughing, choking)

26:09.335 --> 26:11.037
MAN:
Whoa, is he okay?

26:11.037 --> 26:13.640
Don't worry, everything's
gonna be okay.

26:19.746 --> 26:21.347
(loud cough, girl squeals)

26:22.882 --> 26:24.651
GIRL:
Is he breathing?

26:24.651 --> 26:26.753
BOY:
He's moving...

26:26.753 --> 26:28.655
BOY 2: Should we
call an ambulance?

26:30.422 --> 26:32.625
(giggling)

26:32.625 --> 26:34.526
(laughing)

26:34.526 --> 26:36.696
Oh, you idiot!

26:36.696 --> 26:40.633
You were supposed to kiss her,
lip lock-- that was the plan!

26:40.633 --> 26:43.469
(crowd laughing)

26:43.469 --> 26:45.371
* *

26:45.371 --> 26:47.907
(laughter continues)

26:49.676 --> 26:52.745
(acoustic guitar plays intro)

27:01.420 --> 27:04.023
* *

27:13.766 --> 27:16.302
* *

27:25.244 --> 27:26.713
* How *

27:26.713 --> 27:29.949
* Does it feel *

27:29.949 --> 27:32.284
* To treat me *

27:32.284 --> 27:34.086
* Like you do? *

27:35.054 --> 27:39.091
* When you laid your hands
upon me *

27:40.459 --> 27:42.929
* And told me *

27:42.929 --> 27:46.032
* Who you are *

27:46.032 --> 27:50.937
* I thought I was mistaken *

27:50.937 --> 27:54.173
* I thought I heard your words *

27:55.207 --> 27:57.609
(thumping)

27:57.609 --> 28:01.280
(song continues faintly
over earphones)

28:17.629 --> 28:20.066
* *

28:27.273 --> 28:29.441
* *

28:40.319 --> 28:42.755
* *

28:46.759 --> 28:48.828
(door creaks)

28:59.806 --> 29:01.874
I'm looking forward
to the journey,

29:01.874 --> 29:04.643
and I don't care
if a woman unaccompanied

29:04.643 --> 29:06.745
is considered to be shameful.

29:06.745 --> 29:10.349
I... I've done nothing wrong.

29:10.349 --> 29:12.919
My heart is...

29:12.919 --> 29:14.453
MAN:
Yes?

29:14.453 --> 29:16.022
Your heart is...?

29:16.022 --> 29:19.525
DIRECTOR: Cut.
DEHLIA (sighs): Uh...

29:19.525 --> 29:20.659
Sorry.

29:20.659 --> 29:23.129
(indistinct chatter)

29:23.129 --> 29:25.531
DIRECTOR:
And... action.

29:28.500 --> 29:31.770
I'm looking forward
to the journey, and...

29:31.770 --> 29:34.673
I don't care that...
(panting)

29:34.673 --> 29:35.908
I feel sick.

29:35.908 --> 29:38.110
I need to stop.
Cut.

29:38.110 --> 29:40.012
(indistinct chatter)

29:40.012 --> 29:41.747
ASSISTANT:
Quiet, please!

29:41.747 --> 29:42.815
(beeping on film)

29:42.815 --> 29:43.850
(gasps)

29:43.850 --> 29:46.252
What are you doing?

29:46.252 --> 29:47.486
I-I-I'm sorry.

29:47.486 --> 29:49.655
DEHLIA: I'm looking forward
to the journey...

29:49.655 --> 29:51.057
That door was unlocked.

29:51.057 --> 29:52.691
Um, the shutters
had rusted closed,

29:52.691 --> 29:54.861
and the bulbs
were all burnt out.

29:54.861 --> 29:56.762
Well, leave it on.

29:56.762 --> 29:58.564
Well...

30:02.268 --> 30:05.938
I haven't been here
since the night she...

30:07.273 --> 30:10.242
You were here
the night she died?

30:12.044 --> 30:14.346
How long did you work for her?

30:14.346 --> 30:16.348
The year
I got out of the service,

30:16.348 --> 30:18.217
I went to work at the studio.

30:18.217 --> 30:21.753
They sent me over here
to project a film for her,

30:21.753 --> 30:26.625
and she asked me to stay
and take care of her, so I did.

30:26.625 --> 30:29.161
That was 1971.

30:29.161 --> 30:33.565
When she disappeared,
did you know where she was?

30:34.901 --> 30:36.602
No.

30:38.104 --> 30:40.072
She never married,

30:40.072 --> 30:43.209
and she seemed to be
very private,

30:43.209 --> 30:45.912
but there must have been a...

30:45.912 --> 30:48.114
there must have been a man...

30:48.114 --> 30:50.316
someone she loved?

30:51.783 --> 30:53.219
(exhales)

30:53.219 --> 30:56.855
Every man who met her
fell in love with her.

30:57.689 --> 30:59.959
It just couldn't be helped.

31:02.361 --> 31:06.232
I just don't know
if she ever felt love herself.

31:06.232 --> 31:09.201
(quiet, mysterious theme
playing)

31:12.939 --> 31:15.307
(crickets chirping
outside)

31:26.018 --> 31:28.320
* *

31:35.861 --> 31:38.130
* *

31:45.837 --> 31:48.207
* *

31:57.416 --> 31:58.750
Hi.

31:58.750 --> 32:02.721
Yeah, I'm sorry about
the weirdness the other day.

32:02.721 --> 32:07.559
I have to say, my feelings were
a little bruised, but, um,

32:07.559 --> 32:08.827
thank you, Corky.

32:08.827 --> 32:11.030
An apology is the sign
of a gentleman.

32:11.030 --> 32:12.531
Inga wrote me in
to the shenanigans.

32:12.531 --> 32:15.167
She's my sister, but I also
think she might be the Devil.

32:15.167 --> 32:17.436
Also, you know,
I thought if you gave me

32:17.436 --> 32:19.305
mouth-to-mouth,
it would be a fantastic way

32:19.305 --> 32:21.540
for us to get
to know each other.

32:21.540 --> 32:23.542
The truth is,

32:23.542 --> 32:24.676
you're awesome.

32:24.676 --> 32:26.078
By the way,

32:26.078 --> 32:27.613
did you know there's
a mystery to this house?

32:27.613 --> 32:30.316
I know.

32:30.316 --> 32:32.218
I only recently discovered

32:32.218 --> 32:34.486
that movies aren't shot
from beginning to end.

32:34.486 --> 32:37.256
So I took the last movie
she ever made

32:37.256 --> 32:38.490
and reassembled the shots

32:38.490 --> 32:41.727
in the order
they were photographed.

32:43.662 --> 32:46.365
CORKY:
O... kay.

32:46.365 --> 32:49.001
I just noticed
something strange.

32:49.001 --> 32:51.070
The last month before
she disappeared,

32:51.070 --> 32:53.705
she's only shown from here up.

32:57.109 --> 32:59.345
Maybe she was pregnant.

32:59.345 --> 33:01.947
She didn't have any kids--
never married

33:01.947 --> 33:04.483
and no kids.
It's just a hunch.

33:04.483 --> 33:07.353
Also, the photograph
in this magazine

33:07.353 --> 33:08.954
is dated just
after her reappearance.

33:08.954 --> 33:10.589
There's an "X" on her robe.

33:10.589 --> 33:13.659
I believe that insignia will
tell us where she was hiding.

33:13.659 --> 33:15.527
I've called all
the hospitals

33:15.527 --> 33:17.996
and hotels that include
the letter "X" in it,

33:17.996 --> 33:19.531
but, so far, nothing.

33:19.531 --> 33:21.833
(sighs):
I need to talk to someone

33:21.833 --> 33:23.335
who's an expert in clothing.

33:23.335 --> 33:25.437
Oh, and one
more thing.

33:25.437 --> 33:30.142
She's often with this man,
but he's always obscured.

33:30.142 --> 33:32.144
A hand at the edge of a picture,

33:32.144 --> 33:33.812
a silhouette,

33:33.812 --> 33:36.082
even a blur.

33:36.082 --> 33:38.484
I think she called him Z.

33:38.484 --> 33:41.120
I have to find out
who this man is.

33:42.154 --> 33:44.590
I just have to solve this case.

33:44.590 --> 33:45.957
(sighs)

33:45.957 --> 33:47.859
What do you think?

33:47.859 --> 33:49.461
I think the ability to sleuth

33:49.461 --> 33:51.997
is an attractive quality
in a woman.

33:51.997 --> 33:53.799
Mm.

33:56.735 --> 33:57.703
(window bangs)

34:01.307 --> 34:03.875
Hey, don't they have
a costume department

34:03.875 --> 34:05.444
on the set of
every film?

34:05.444 --> 34:07.146
Yeah, but you should know
that movie people

34:07.146 --> 34:08.580
are kind of crazy.

34:08.580 --> 34:10.482
Oh, goodness, how
crazy can they be?

34:10.482 --> 34:12.484
Really crazy.

34:16.054 --> 34:17.054
You're fine.

34:17.054 --> 34:18.190
Oh, I just had a question.

34:18.190 --> 34:19.925
And I'm all out of answers.

34:19.925 --> 34:21.159
You look '50s.

34:21.159 --> 34:22.428
Go to set.

34:22.428 --> 34:23.629
But I was just wondering
if maybe...

34:23.629 --> 34:24.630
Now!

34:24.630 --> 34:26.431
Here we go! Okay,
we're moving.

34:26.431 --> 34:28.199
We're moving, people!
We're on our way!

34:28.199 --> 34:30.902
We are moving!

34:30.902 --> 34:32.103
I, eh... uh...

34:34.739 --> 34:37.042
All right, let's just
shoot the rehearsal.

34:37.042 --> 34:39.710
Has anybody seen
Mr. Fancy Pants?

34:39.710 --> 34:41.713
Right here, you idiot.

34:41.713 --> 34:42.547
(chuckles)

34:42.547 --> 34:44.150
Nickname. I love
a nickname.

34:44.150 --> 34:46.685
Not a nickname, Andy,
it's not a nickname.

34:46.685 --> 34:48.353
You really are an idiot.

34:48.353 --> 34:49.788
Oh, all right,
all right.

34:49.788 --> 34:50.755
I, um, uh...

34:50.755 --> 34:52.056
Okay, we're shooting
the rehearsal!

34:52.056 --> 34:53.891
Excuse me,
sir, no, sir.

34:53.891 --> 34:55.127
No, I...

34:55.127 --> 34:57.229
By the way, it's "action,"

34:57.229 --> 34:59.998
not "begin the acting."

34:59.998 --> 35:01.700
Action.
Locking it up!

35:01.700 --> 35:03.935
Last looks everybody!
Last looks!

35:03.935 --> 35:05.871
Walking away! Walking away!
Quiet, please!

35:05.871 --> 35:09.808
And we're rolling!

35:09.808 --> 35:11.210
Oh, you're cute.

35:11.210 --> 35:12.878
(chuckles):
Thank you.

35:12.878 --> 35:14.880
Okay, you hate crime.

35:14.880 --> 35:15.947
And action!

35:15.947 --> 35:19.985
Hold him right there, boys.

35:19.985 --> 35:22.254
Spider Winetrap.

35:22.254 --> 35:24.656
As I live and breathe.

35:24.656 --> 35:26.492
You have the right
to remain silent.

35:26.492 --> 35:28.294
You have the right
to an attorney.

35:28.294 --> 35:30.028
Excuse me, I'm sorry, but...

35:30.028 --> 35:31.330
What?
I'm sorry.

35:31.330 --> 35:33.232
This just feels inauthentic.

35:33.232 --> 35:35.000
Feels what?
Well, the scene takes place

35:35.000 --> 35:37.903
in the '50s, but you're reading
Miranda to the suspect.

35:37.903 --> 35:39.738
Um, excuse me!

35:39.738 --> 35:42.073
Why in the name
of sweet Christmas

35:42.073 --> 35:44.310
is this tiny person talking?!

35:46.312 --> 35:48.614
Well, reading of Miranda
upon arrest wasn't law

35:48.614 --> 35:50.182
until '63.

35:50.182 --> 35:51.517
Is that right?

35:51.517 --> 35:54.052
The scene is still
delicious either way.

35:54.052 --> 35:56.154
What's your name?

35:56.154 --> 35:57.189
Uh, Nancy Drew.

35:57.189 --> 35:58.590
I'm Bruce.

35:58.590 --> 36:00.259
All right,
I'll tell you what,

36:00.259 --> 36:01.727
why don't you
direct the movie,

36:01.727 --> 36:03.061
Nancy Drew?

36:03.061 --> 36:04.363
(grunts)

36:04.363 --> 36:06.765
(laughter)

36:06.765 --> 36:10.902
Listen, Nancy, would you,
would you consider, you know,

36:10.902 --> 36:13.405
directing this film?

36:13.405 --> 36:15.941
'Cause we can get rid
of this guy in a second.

36:15.941 --> 36:19.345
Is there a law against common
courtesy in Los Angeles?

36:19.345 --> 36:20.946
Courtesy is
so awesome.

36:20.946 --> 36:22.248
I'm really into it.

36:22.248 --> 36:23.849
In my book, courtesy counts.

36:23.849 --> 36:26.518
I'd like to read
that book, Nancy.

36:34.393 --> 36:37.329
It's not an "X";
they're palm trees.

36:37.329 --> 36:39.365
Okay.

36:39.365 --> 36:41.467
What does that mean?

36:44.270 --> 36:45.971
NANCY:
The insignia on her robe.

36:45.971 --> 36:49.475
It's, um...

36:49.475 --> 36:51.443
something "Palms."

36:51.443 --> 36:53.479
Oh, now I get it.

36:53.479 --> 36:54.713
Just kidding,
I don't.

36:54.713 --> 36:58.250
Southern Pines,
California Hot Springs...

36:59.318 --> 37:02.554
Twin Palms Bungalows and Spa.

37:12.764 --> 37:14.800
* *

37:18.069 --> 37:21.172
There was a fire
some 20 years ago

37:21.172 --> 37:22.674
and all the records
were burned.

37:22.674 --> 37:24.443
And on top of that,
I'm afraid

37:24.443 --> 37:26.312
our guest list
is confidential.

37:26.312 --> 37:28.079
Oh.

37:28.079 --> 37:29.315
(sighs)

37:30.248 --> 37:33.285
Where's the closest hospital?

37:35.821 --> 37:38.790
All the children born
in one week, 24 years ago?

37:38.790 --> 37:39.858
Yes.

37:39.858 --> 37:41.993
Well, all the ones
given up for adoption.

37:41.993 --> 37:44.630
See, the birth mother, she may
have left money for the child...

37:44.630 --> 37:46.732
I'm sorry, but those
records are sealed.

37:46.732 --> 37:48.900
Only a court order can
open those records,

37:48.900 --> 37:51.069
and even then, only by a
child seeking a parent.

37:51.069 --> 37:52.070
Are you the child?

37:52.070 --> 37:53.439
No.

37:55.006 --> 37:56.408
But, um, thank you anyway.

38:00.245 --> 38:03.048
Here's a blondie
for your trouble.

38:12.824 --> 38:16.027
(low, indistinct
conversation)

38:23.769 --> 38:25.737
Did... did you make these?

38:26.738 --> 38:29.675
No, Hannah our housekeeper,

38:29.675 --> 38:31.009
back in
River Heights, did.

38:31.009 --> 38:33.111
She sent over a tin.

38:33.111 --> 38:34.680
She's a wonderful baker.

38:34.680 --> 38:37.349
It's so weird-- my mother
made these when I was a kid.

38:37.349 --> 38:38.884
I-I haven't had one in years.

38:43.622 --> 38:45.824
It's so perfectly moist.

38:47.826 --> 38:48.860
Come here.

38:56.802 --> 39:00.271
The county... recommends
a pediatrician

39:00.271 --> 39:02.374
to new adoptive
parents.

39:02.374 --> 39:05.043
The doctor's files
aren't sealed.

39:05.043 --> 39:06.044
This might help.

39:08.514 --> 39:09.981
Thank you.

39:09.981 --> 39:12.418
And you didn't
get that from me.

39:14.553 --> 39:17.723
24 years ago.

39:17.723 --> 39:18.590
Wow.

39:18.590 --> 39:20.225
That is so long ago.

39:20.225 --> 39:24.930
Yes. It would have been a
first appointment-- a newborn.

39:24.930 --> 39:27.298
I know it seems
a little disorgani-zized,

39:27.298 --> 39:31.437
but I know where
everything is.

39:31.437 --> 39:33.639
(laughs)

39:35.741 --> 39:39.077
(whispers):
Oh... Ow...

39:39.077 --> 39:40.078
Right there.

39:40.078 --> 39:41.079
Here it is.

39:41.079 --> 39:43.649
There were two newborns
that week...

39:43.649 --> 39:45.784
No, make that three.

39:45.784 --> 39:49.588
Oh, but, uh, I don't think
I can release any information.

39:49.588 --> 39:51.056
Let me call headquarters.
(phone ringing)

39:51.056 --> 39:52.190
Oh!

39:52.190 --> 39:53.825
Maybe that's them.

39:53.825 --> 39:55.293
Hello.
Hi, Carol, it's Jimmy.

39:55.293 --> 39:56.895
Oh, Jimmy.

39:56.895 --> 39:59.297
Yeah, no, I was looking for it,
and I found it, I found it.

39:59.297 --> 40:01.299
I did find it
and it... Oh.

40:01.299 --> 40:03.401
That's not it,
but it's pink and, uh,

40:03.401 --> 40:05.871
it wasn't, no, it wasn't where
I thought it was going to be,

40:05.871 --> 40:07.473
because it's...
JIMMY: I think it's yellow.

40:07.473 --> 40:08.574
I put it somewhere else.

40:08.574 --> 40:09.941
Yeah, oh, boy.
Oh, boy.

40:09.941 --> 40:11.543
I'm going to have
to call you back.

40:11.543 --> 40:12.811
JIMMY:
Can you get it to me?

40:12.811 --> 40:15.447
I'm going to have
to call you back.

40:15.447 --> 40:17.382
Nice try, squirt.

40:17.382 --> 40:19.150
Nice try.

40:19.150 --> 40:20.819
(into to "Nice Day"
by Persephone's Bee's playing)

40:20.819 --> 40:22.654
* On a nice day *

40:24.623 --> 40:25.991
* On a nice day *

40:29.461 --> 40:31.196
* I don't care what they say *

40:32.898 --> 40:35.834
* I don't care what they say *

40:35.834 --> 40:38.003
* On a nice day *

40:39.805 --> 40:42.040
* On a nice day *

40:46.478 --> 40:47.746
* On a... *

40:47.746 --> 40:50.682
Hello, I'm looking
for Jane Brighton.

40:51.483 --> 40:52.751
Are you Jane Brighton?

40:52.751 --> 40:54.886
Are you Martine Dahlberg?

40:54.886 --> 40:56.555
Yeah. Why?

40:56.555 --> 40:58.790
I was just wondering,
were you adopted?

40:58.790 --> 41:00.225
Are you Susan Thabit?

41:00.225 --> 41:01.326
Uh-huh.

41:01.326 --> 41:02.761
Were you adopted?

41:02.761 --> 41:04.329
Are you Martine Dahlberg?

41:04.329 --> 41:05.396
Yes.

41:05.396 --> 41:06.431
Were you adopted?

41:06.431 --> 41:08.266
Hello, um...

41:08.266 --> 41:09.434
Can I help you?

41:09.434 --> 41:11.603
Sorry, no.

41:13.171 --> 41:14.840
No.

41:15.373 --> 41:16.575
No.

41:16.575 --> 41:17.609
(sighs)

41:17.609 --> 41:19.678
No.
No.

41:21.012 --> 41:23.148
No.
No.

41:23.949 --> 41:25.316
No.

41:25.316 --> 41:26.785
Uh-uh.

41:28.453 --> 41:30.221
No.
No.

41:30.221 --> 41:31.389
Nope.

41:31.389 --> 41:33.458
-No. -No. -No.
-No. -No. -No.

41:33.458 --> 41:35.661
(baby crying in distance)

41:40.465 --> 41:41.533
(knocking)

41:41.533 --> 41:42.801
Hello?

41:42.801 --> 41:45.503
Um, is there
a Jane Brighton here?

41:45.503 --> 41:46.605
(sighs)

41:46.605 --> 41:49.274
That depends on who's asking.

41:49.274 --> 41:51.176
Were you adopted?

41:53.178 --> 41:55.213
Yeah.

41:59.250 --> 42:01.286
Who are you?

42:07.425 --> 42:09.160
You're who I'm looking for.

42:09.160 --> 42:10.962
I am?

42:13.031 --> 42:14.600
Hi.

42:19.738 --> 42:22.207
You're kidding.

42:22.207 --> 42:24.710
Did your parents tell you
that you were adopted?

42:24.710 --> 42:26.712
It wasn't hard to figure out.

42:26.712 --> 42:28.546
I mean, I didn't look
anything like them.

42:28.546 --> 42:29.848
My mother passed away,

42:29.848 --> 42:33.518
and then my father, um...

42:33.518 --> 42:34.886
I had to get away from him.

42:34.886 --> 42:38.223
Uh, I left home early.

42:39.257 --> 42:41.359
Dehlia Draycott!

42:41.359 --> 42:43.862
Wow.

42:43.862 --> 42:46.031
Dehlia may have made
a provision for you.

42:46.031 --> 42:47.666
If we can prove
that you're her daughter,

42:47.666 --> 42:48.934
there may be some money.

42:50.769 --> 42:53.438
Is this some kind of
a practical joke?

42:53.438 --> 42:54.640
Oh, no.

42:54.640 --> 42:56.675
I don't joke.

42:56.675 --> 42:58.276
CORKY:
I get that a lot.

42:58.276 --> 43:00.646
I'm 12, but I skipped
a few grades.

43:00.646 --> 43:02.147
NANCY: Because you were
ahead academically?

43:02.147 --> 43:03.348
Heck no.

43:03.348 --> 43:05.016
There just wasn't any
action in junior high,

43:05.016 --> 43:07.786
so my dad made
a few calls.

43:07.786 --> 43:09.387
Anyway, I was, uh,
wondering if we could do,

43:09.387 --> 43:12.323
like, a dinner thing,
like, Saturday-ish?

43:12.323 --> 43:13.625
Not a date.

43:13.625 --> 43:15.493
Corky, you've been
really nice to me...

43:15.493 --> 43:18.163
I'll show you the sights,
and we'll have a few laughs.

43:18.163 --> 43:20.331
But there's this guy
back in River Heights.

43:20.331 --> 43:22.868
Oh. Ouch. Okay.

43:22.868 --> 43:25.937
Well, you still need to
eat, and it's not a date.

43:25.937 --> 43:28.339
Okay, seeing as how
it's not a date...

43:28.339 --> 43:29.875
(gasps)

43:30.876 --> 43:33.178
(tires screeching)

43:37.582 --> 43:40.686
Go! Go, go, go, go!

43:40.686 --> 43:42.520
They almost hit us.
Hurry!

43:42.520 --> 43:43.621
Go, go, go, go, go!

43:43.621 --> 43:45.657
Hey. Hey!

43:48.293 --> 43:50.528
I wonder who
tried to kill us.

43:50.528 --> 43:51.897
Yeah, I'm wondering
that, too.

43:51.897 --> 43:54.332
In fact, I'm kind of
freaking out about it!

43:54.332 --> 43:56.167
Well...

43:56.167 --> 43:57.803
usually when someone
tries to kill me,

43:57.803 --> 43:59.938
it's because
I'm on to something.

43:59.938 --> 44:01.206
Oh, you have a cut.

44:02.607 --> 44:05.844
There were dealer plates
on the SUV.

44:05.844 --> 44:08.379
I made note of the make,
year and model.

44:08.379 --> 44:10.548
Plus the damage sustained
from hitting the barrier

44:10.548 --> 44:11.917
could help us
identify it, too.

44:15.887 --> 44:18.023
You're just not like
the other girls, Nancy.

44:23.328 --> 44:25.363
(sighs)

44:27.598 --> 44:29.200
(phone rings)

44:29.200 --> 44:30.535
Hello?

44:30.535 --> 44:34.773
MAN: Do not look into
this Dehlia Draycott business.

44:34.773 --> 44:37.475
If you proceed,
you will be harmed.

44:37.475 --> 44:39.945
Oh.
Do you understand?

44:39.945 --> 44:42.480
We're not interested
in mud slide insurance,

44:42.480 --> 44:43.849
but, um, thank you for calling.

44:43.849 --> 44:45.250
Have a nice day.

44:45.250 --> 44:46.251
(phone beeps off)

44:57.628 --> 44:59.731
Whoa, what's this?

44:59.731 --> 45:00.899
I apologize, sir.

45:00.899 --> 45:02.100
Allow me to
introduce myself.

45:02.100 --> 45:04.035
My name is
Nancy Drew.

45:04.035 --> 45:05.403
It's very nice to make
your acquaintance.

45:05.403 --> 45:07.238
I've been trying to
set up an appointment

45:07.238 --> 45:09.174
with your office, but, um...
Posture, eye contact.

45:09.174 --> 45:11.977
Pay attention, people--
that's breeding.

45:11.977 --> 45:13.611
I-I was just
wondering

45:13.611 --> 45:16.314
if I could have five minutes
to discuss something with you.

45:16.314 --> 45:17.682
Anytime at all.

45:17.682 --> 45:19.017
Here's my card.

45:20.786 --> 45:23.121
(chuckles)

45:23.121 --> 45:24.122
Oh.

45:26.758 --> 45:28.960
Thank you.

45:28.960 --> 45:31.162
It's about one of your
clients, a movie star.

45:31.162 --> 45:35.233
(chuckles): All my clients
are movie stars, muffin.

45:35.233 --> 45:37.568
Well, I may have found some
evidence suggesting that...

45:37.568 --> 45:38.636
Astonishing.

45:38.636 --> 45:40.538
Um, it may
imply that...

45:40.538 --> 45:42.140
Absolutely astonishing.

45:42.140 --> 45:44.943
As I was
saying, um...

45:44.943 --> 45:46.744
I'm very disappointed, Senator.

45:46.744 --> 45:48.914
Well, as you know,
you do owe me

45:48.914 --> 45:52.417
a favor or two.

45:52.417 --> 45:54.886
Well, talk to somebody
else on your staff.

45:54.886 --> 45:56.187
Maybe they
can help you.

46:00.225 --> 46:01.126
(knocking)

46:01.126 --> 46:02.560
Jane, are you there?

46:02.560 --> 46:04.395
(locks clicking)

46:04.395 --> 46:05.730
Hi.

46:05.730 --> 46:07.899
I saw the lawyers who represent
the estate today, and...

46:07.899 --> 46:09.935
It's all right,
I don't need any help.

46:09.935 --> 46:11.469
What do you mean?

46:11.469 --> 46:13.471
Don't you want to know if
you're Dehlia's daughter?

46:13.471 --> 46:14.840
Just leave us alone, okay?

46:16.041 --> 46:18.143
You seem like
a really nice person.

46:18.143 --> 46:19.177
I'm sorry.

46:21.913 --> 46:23.114
(lock clicks)

46:28.586 --> 46:30.355
(owl hooting, crickets chirping)

46:38.729 --> 46:41.566
The will is in
the Chinese box.

46:41.566 --> 46:44.970
So there is a will.

46:55.380 --> 46:59.317
* *

46:59.317 --> 47:01.552
(voices playing over laptop)

47:09.027 --> 47:11.629
Miss Draycott
collected chinoiserie.

47:11.629 --> 47:14.632
Last year, the owner sold off
the most valuable pieces,

47:14.632 --> 47:16.067
against my wishes.

47:16.067 --> 47:19.037
Do you remember
the name of the dealer?

47:19.037 --> 47:21.439
You ask a lot
of questions.

47:21.439 --> 47:22.273
Is it this place?

47:22.273 --> 47:23.841
I noticed the ad was circled.

47:23.841 --> 47:25.911
Do they have the box?

47:25.911 --> 47:27.678
Let me tell you
something, young lady.

47:27.678 --> 47:29.915
Everyone who has tried to
piece this thing together

47:29.915 --> 47:31.316
has run into trouble.

47:31.316 --> 47:34.452
(phone ringing)

47:34.452 --> 47:35.853
Hello?

47:35.853 --> 47:39.024
So you should be getting
an early birthday present

47:39.024 --> 47:42.160
"slash" reward thing,
for going along with

47:42.160 --> 47:44.896
my no sleuthing law
in California thing.

47:44.896 --> 47:46.231
Dad, you shouldn't have.

47:46.231 --> 47:48.366
I don't really deserve it.

47:48.366 --> 47:49.434
Yes, you do.

47:49.434 --> 47:50.468
(doorbell ringing)

47:50.468 --> 47:52.137
I know it hasn't
been easy for you,

47:52.137 --> 47:54.139
and this will make me feel
a little less guilty.

47:54.139 --> 47:57.042
What, what is it?

47:57.042 --> 47:58.910
Ah, just walk outside.

48:00.611 --> 48:02.180
Hi.

48:02.180 --> 48:03.581
My sister dropped me off,

48:03.581 --> 48:05.416
and now she won't
go away.

48:06.251 --> 48:07.518
Leave!

48:07.518 --> 48:09.120
My roadster.

48:09.120 --> 48:10.655
Dad, how did you get it here?

48:10.655 --> 48:12.457
Happy almost your birthday.

48:12.457 --> 48:13.258
Ned!

48:13.258 --> 48:15.060
You drove this all the way here?

48:15.060 --> 48:18.029
Uh, yeah, wouldn't fit
in my suitcase.

48:18.029 --> 48:21.032
I've missed this car so much.

48:21.032 --> 48:23.935
And you-- I've missed
the car and you.

48:25.436 --> 48:27.105
Oh, uh, Ned,

48:27.105 --> 48:28.406
Corky, Corky, Ned.

48:28.406 --> 48:30.575
Ned is my...

48:30.575 --> 48:33.211
really good friend

48:33.211 --> 48:34.745
from River Heights.

48:34.745 --> 48:36.214
River Heights,
right.

48:36.214 --> 48:38.216
That's in one of
those flyover states.

48:38.216 --> 48:40.685
Did I interrupt something?

48:40.685 --> 48:43.321
Yes, actually, you did.

48:44.990 --> 48:46.691
CARSON:
Hello? Hello?

48:46.691 --> 48:47.792
Oh, Dad.
CARSON: Nancy?

48:47.792 --> 48:48.994
Thank you so much.

48:48.994 --> 48:50.228
We have to go.

48:50.228 --> 48:51.429
(phone beeps off)

48:53.231 --> 48:56.301
Corky's going on
a date with her?

48:56.301 --> 48:57.202
Whoa.

48:57.202 --> 49:00.338
Nancy weirdo has,
like, two dates.

49:00.338 --> 49:03.274
Oh. That other
one is cute.

49:03.274 --> 49:04.642
I mean, I don't
usually go for

49:04.642 --> 49:07.112
the "just back from slopping
the hogs" type, but...

49:07.112 --> 49:08.613
(chuckles)
he's cute.

49:08.613 --> 49:10.315
("The Delicate Place"
rock intro playing)

49:10.315 --> 49:14.085
* Have you got the answer? *

49:14.085 --> 49:19.490
* Have I yet won the part? *

49:19.490 --> 49:25.096
* Is this just your way
of breaking my heart? *

49:29.134 --> 49:31.969
Hello. Would you like
to order some drinks?

49:31.969 --> 49:34.439
I'll have a glass
of milk, please.

49:34.439 --> 49:35.240
Ah, milk--

49:35.240 --> 49:37.142
how refreshingly wholesome.

49:37.142 --> 49:39.077
I'll have the exact same thing.

49:39.077 --> 49:41.412
Who is this person?

49:41.412 --> 49:44.082
Nancy and I met,
and things just clicked.

49:44.082 --> 49:46.917
We laugh, we talk,
we keep it real.

49:46.917 --> 49:48.686
We're basically
best friends.

49:48.686 --> 49:51.656
It's funny that
she never mentioned you.

49:53.124 --> 49:54.492
Hey, buddy,

49:54.492 --> 49:56.127
she wants your drink order.

49:56.127 --> 49:59.697
Um, can I get
an iced latte?

49:59.697 --> 50:02.867
No latte in
Chinese restaurant, silly.

50:02.867 --> 50:04.135
Yeah, silly.
Excuse me...?

50:04.135 --> 50:07.638
No latte in
the Chinese restaurant.

50:07.638 --> 50:08.806
Don't talk
to me, okay?

50:08.806 --> 50:10.141
NANCY:
All right.

50:10.141 --> 50:11.542
Wow, this is fun, huh?

50:11.542 --> 50:12.810
Um, you know,

50:12.810 --> 50:14.645
Ned and I have known each other
since second grade.

50:14.645 --> 50:16.447
He helped me
solve the mystery

50:16.447 --> 50:18.015
of the missing
chalkboard erasers.

50:18.015 --> 50:20.017
It was a janitor.

50:20.017 --> 50:22.353
Ooh, fantastic!

50:23.154 --> 50:25.990
Oh, my gosh.

50:25.990 --> 50:27.892
How funny.
(chuckles)

50:27.892 --> 50:30.061
Here we are and here you are.

50:30.061 --> 50:31.662
Hi. What's your name?

50:31.662 --> 50:32.663
Ned?

50:32.663 --> 50:34.632
You're not sure?

50:34.632 --> 50:35.600
No.

50:35.600 --> 50:37.602
I mean, yeah,
yes, I'm sure.

50:37.602 --> 50:40.905
Why are you here?
Why are you here?

50:40.905 --> 50:42.107
Why are you here?

50:42.107 --> 50:44.909
Hey, hey, guys,
don't gang up on me.

50:44.909 --> 50:46.744
I'm sensitive.

50:56.821 --> 50:58.389
(door bells jingling)

50:58.389 --> 50:59.824
Hello.

50:59.824 --> 51:01.126
I'm looking for a box.

51:01.126 --> 51:02.993
That is, one in particular.

51:02.993 --> 51:04.929
What kind of box?

51:04.929 --> 51:07.098
Um, Chinese.

51:07.932 --> 51:13.371
Well... you've come
to the right place.

51:13.371 --> 51:16.441
So this is why
you wanted Chinese food.

51:16.441 --> 51:18.409
What are you guys
doing in here?

51:18.409 --> 51:20.345
This is so nonlinear.

51:20.345 --> 51:23.181
Everybody pick a row,
check inside each box.

51:23.181 --> 51:25.150
We're looking for a will.

51:26.651 --> 51:28.386
(kids chattering)

51:28.386 --> 51:29.654
Wait, what's over there?
Hey.

51:29.654 --> 51:31.556
CORKY:
Guys, did you see this box yet?

51:31.556 --> 51:33.224
Nothing there.
Whoa.

51:33.224 --> 51:35.760
No, no, no, don't...
don't touch.

51:35.760 --> 51:38.763
Hey, hey, watch this top.

51:38.763 --> 51:40.231
That is very expensive.

51:40.231 --> 51:43.468
* I'm too insistent
like nobody showed me *

51:43.468 --> 51:44.969
* How to keep relationships *

51:44.969 --> 51:47.104
CORKY:
Did you see this?

51:47.104 --> 51:48.906
It's big.
Put that down.

51:48.906 --> 51:50.875
(playful growling)

51:50.875 --> 51:52.143
(screams)

51:52.143 --> 51:53.478
What? What, you
think you're funny?

51:53.478 --> 51:55.780
Do you think
you're funny?

51:55.780 --> 51:58.216
So not cute.

52:01.051 --> 52:03.288
There is one more.

52:08.092 --> 52:10.395
(quiet, ominous tones playing)

52:16.667 --> 52:19.770
So, Nance...

52:19.770 --> 52:21.772
what's the deal
with you and Ned?

52:21.772 --> 52:23.508
(faint beeping)
Do you hear something?

52:23.508 --> 52:25.876
No, I mean, are you
two, like, a thing?

52:25.876 --> 52:27.077
(beeping)

52:27.077 --> 52:28.246
Um...

52:28.246 --> 52:30.014
Excuse me, I have
to defuse this bomb.

52:30.014 --> 52:31.081
No kidding.

52:31.081 --> 52:33.184
Love is a
battlefield.

52:33.184 --> 52:37.522
(suspenseful theme playing)

52:57.107 --> 52:59.344
* *

53:08.953 --> 53:13.190
* *

53:22.833 --> 53:25.836
* *

53:35.179 --> 53:38.383
(quiet, gentle theme plays)

53:43.388 --> 53:47.358
(car door shuts,
engine starts)

53:49.394 --> 53:51.496
(onlookers shouting)

53:53.298 --> 53:55.633
That's the SUV
that tried to run us down!

53:55.633 --> 53:57.468
The side's damaged.
Come on.

53:57.468 --> 53:58.736
What was that?
Are you okay?

53:58.736 --> 53:59.970
What was that?
NED: Hurry, we're losing them.

53:59.970 --> 54:02.707
Oh, so you meant
literally a bomb.

54:02.707 --> 54:05.109
What was that?
What was that? Are you okay?

54:05.109 --> 54:06.844
(sirens blaring)
Hello?

54:06.844 --> 54:08.245
(tires screeching)

54:10.014 --> 54:12.450
(man shouting in Chinese)

54:12.450 --> 54:13.484
They turned up that street.

54:13.484 --> 54:14.785
CORKY:
Hold on a sec.

54:14.785 --> 54:16.321
I thought we were
driving away from them.

54:16.321 --> 54:17.788
That's the only reason
why I got in the car.

54:17.788 --> 54:19.857
Buckled up?
I'm fine.

54:19.857 --> 54:22.560
(tires screeching)

54:23.127 --> 54:24.329
Buckling up.

54:31.836 --> 54:33.404
Say we actually do
catch up with them,

54:33.404 --> 54:34.439
what happens then?

54:34.439 --> 54:36.240
Seriously.

54:36.240 --> 54:38.476
It really gets my goat when
someone tries to kill me.

54:38.476 --> 54:39.477
It's so rude.

54:39.477 --> 54:40.811
But it only makes me

54:40.811 --> 54:42.713
want to try harder.
Then let the horses run!

54:42.713 --> 54:45.683
We will go the posted
speed limit and no faster.

54:46.884 --> 54:48.719
No!

54:51.556 --> 54:54.359
Everybody in the universe drives
over the speed limit, Nancy.

54:54.359 --> 54:55.693
What Nancy's trying to say is

54:55.693 --> 54:57.362
that the ends do not
justify the means.

54:57.362 --> 54:58.563
Your means will lose them.

54:58.563 --> 55:00.598
It's important
to judge the ends

55:00.598 --> 55:01.732
and judge the means
independently,

55:01.732 --> 55:03.267
in order to do
what's right.

55:03.267 --> 55:05.503
Didn't you promise your father
that you wouldn't sleuth?

55:06.371 --> 55:08.539
(tires screeching,
horns blaring)

55:09.507 --> 55:11.008
Aren't you breaking
that promise?

55:13.243 --> 55:14.779
(sighs)

55:15.546 --> 55:17.882
What are you going to do?

55:18.616 --> 55:22.453
I have to stop working
on this case.

55:22.453 --> 55:24.622
I have to stop and be normal.

55:27.291 --> 55:29.326
(tires screeching)

55:29.326 --> 55:30.561
(horns blaring)

55:41.305 --> 55:42.607
What's this?

55:42.607 --> 55:45.376
Oh, just normal stuff.

55:45.376 --> 55:46.677
Normal teenage stuff.

55:48.479 --> 55:50.715
Okay, carry on.

55:54.218 --> 55:56.020
Ow! He just
pinched me.

55:56.020 --> 55:57.287
Deal with it.

55:57.287 --> 55:58.989
If we're gonna baby-sit him,
we should get paid.

56:00.791 --> 56:02.660
Ned, why is your shirt
all wrinkled?

56:02.660 --> 56:05.229
'Cause my closet's
six inches deep.

56:05.229 --> 56:06.964
That's not possible.

56:06.964 --> 56:08.533
How could...

56:09.534 --> 56:11.636
Show me.

56:16.273 --> 56:17.842
CORKY:
What are you guys doing?

56:19.644 --> 56:22.146
"Hey, Corky,
we're super glad you asked.

56:22.146 --> 56:24.014
Would you like to tag along?"

56:27.552 --> 56:28.553
Seriously.

56:28.553 --> 56:30.054
Ooh, God!

56:30.054 --> 56:32.022
What is going on?!

56:36.093 --> 56:38.062
I just fell down.

56:40.465 --> 56:42.433
But I'm fine.

56:43.267 --> 56:44.769
(knocking)

56:44.769 --> 56:47.938
I still don't know
what's going on.

56:52.743 --> 56:54.945
Whenever you feel like
letting me know.

57:04.889 --> 57:06.891
(knocking)

57:09.293 --> 57:11.328
(hollow thudding)

57:11.996 --> 57:13.931
(latch clicks,
panel creaks)

57:15.633 --> 57:18.135
A secret passageway.

57:18.135 --> 57:21.472
So this is how the intruder's
been getting upstairs.

57:21.472 --> 57:23.140
This is nuts.

57:23.140 --> 57:25.109
Ned, will you
get my flashlight?

57:25.109 --> 57:26.711
It's in my kit.

57:27.945 --> 57:30.247
Wouldn't this be
considered sleuthing?

57:30.247 --> 57:31.549
Who are we kidding?

57:31.549 --> 57:33.383
I can't stop.

57:33.383 --> 57:35.820
Once I find the will
and determine the identity of Z,

57:35.820 --> 57:37.722
I'll tell my father
everything.

57:37.722 --> 57:39.890
He'll understand.

57:39.890 --> 57:41.792
I mean, how else am I
going to help Jane?

57:43.093 --> 57:44.829
It's important.

57:46.130 --> 57:48.098
Don't you think?

57:48.599 --> 57:50.768
Yeah.

57:54.605 --> 57:57.808
(wood creaking)

58:07.284 --> 58:10.087
(clanking)

58:10.087 --> 58:12.022
(creaking)

58:14.391 --> 58:17.628
(chandeliers jingling)

58:21.098 --> 58:24.535
CORKY (distant):
Uh, what was that?

58:26.537 --> 58:28.706
I think we just
had an earthquake.

58:34.044 --> 58:36.080
Hello?

58:41.351 --> 58:43.788
NED:
Nancy!

58:47.792 --> 58:50.094
Are you all right?

58:50.094 --> 58:51.261
Where are you?

58:51.261 --> 58:53.263
I'm in the basement.

58:58.235 --> 59:00.237
Do you see anything?

59:03.107 --> 59:04.875
I found a tunnel,
and I'm going in.

59:04.875 --> 59:06.143
If I'm not back
in ten minutes,

59:06.143 --> 59:07.645
that means
something bad's happened.

59:07.645 --> 59:09.379
(giggles)

59:09.379 --> 59:11.949
I don't think
that was a joke.

59:21.759 --> 59:23.961
(eerie theme playing)

59:35.773 --> 59:39.009
(humming jauntily)

59:43.280 --> 59:44.615
(screaming)

59:44.615 --> 59:46.316
Hi!

59:48.185 --> 59:50.120
A tunnel?

59:50.120 --> 59:51.989
In the laundry room?

59:51.989 --> 59:54.291
What the hell
is that all about?

59:54.291 --> 59:55.125
John Leshing.

59:55.125 --> 59:56.493
He's a tenant in
this building.

59:56.493 --> 59:57.995
Hmm.

59:57.995 --> 59:59.363
He's the caretaker of the
Dehlia Draycott estate.

59:59.363 --> 01:00:01.699
If anyone knows about
the tunnel, he does.

01:00:01.699 --> 01:00:04.969
That man has always
given me the willies.

01:00:04.969 --> 01:00:07.204
The drowning kittens type.

01:00:07.204 --> 01:00:10.140
You know what I mean?

01:00:19.349 --> 01:00:21.551
Hi. These are for you two.

01:00:21.551 --> 01:00:22.552
Here you go.

01:00:22.552 --> 01:00:23.954
Oh, okay.

01:00:25.756 --> 01:00:27.958
These are for you two.

01:00:33.397 --> 01:00:35.299
I hope you attend.

01:00:36.400 --> 01:00:39.036
(chuckles)

01:00:39.036 --> 01:00:40.838
Wow.

01:00:42.639 --> 01:00:46.043
I know that she's weird,
but we have to go.

01:00:46.043 --> 01:00:47.477
Why?

01:00:47.477 --> 01:00:50.147
Ned, my future husband,
is going to be there.

01:00:54.151 --> 01:00:55.519
(knocking)

01:00:55.519 --> 01:00:57.387
Jane? It's me Nancy.

01:00:57.387 --> 01:01:00.725
I was wondering if you and Allie
wanted to come to a party.

01:01:00.725 --> 01:01:01.926
(knocking)

01:01:13.303 --> 01:01:15.172
Oh, my goodness.

01:01:22.046 --> 01:01:25.482
Wow, guys, your streamers
look great.

01:01:25.482 --> 01:01:27.684
Let's see yours.

01:01:32.957 --> 01:01:35.592
Yeah, yours
are all right.

01:01:35.592 --> 01:01:37.762
NANCY:
Downloading's cool...

01:01:37.762 --> 01:01:39.629
but nothing sounds
like vinyl.

01:01:39.629 --> 01:01:40.931
(Latin dance music playing)

01:01:40.931 --> 01:01:43.000
You couldn't be more right
if you tried, Nancy.

01:01:49.774 --> 01:01:50.975
(doorbell ringing)

01:01:54.378 --> 01:01:55.379
Yeah.

01:01:57.414 --> 01:01:58.215
Hi.
Hi.

01:01:58.215 --> 01:01:59.583
Hey, I brought
a few friends.

01:01:59.583 --> 01:02:01.318
I hope you don't mind,
all right?

01:02:01.318 --> 01:02:02.853
Sure.

01:02:04.688 --> 01:02:06.590
INGA:
Oh.

01:02:06.590 --> 01:02:08.859
I didn't get the memo
about it being a retarded theme.

01:02:08.859 --> 01:02:10.594
(Inga chuckles)

01:02:10.594 --> 01:02:12.162
Hey, Ned.

01:02:12.162 --> 01:02:12.997
Hi.

01:02:12.997 --> 01:02:15.465
Oh, can I take your coat?

01:02:15.465 --> 01:02:16.466
Okay.

01:02:18.302 --> 01:02:20.237
Um, refreshments are
in the dining room.

01:02:20.237 --> 01:02:23.908
We'll be having
a taffy pull later, guys.

01:02:25.275 --> 01:02:26.410
Oh.

01:02:26.410 --> 01:02:27.411
Come on in.

01:02:27.411 --> 01:02:28.478
Hi.
Hi.

01:02:28.478 --> 01:02:30.614
Hi. Refreshments in
the dining room.

01:02:30.614 --> 01:02:32.616
Oh, hello. Hi.

01:02:32.616 --> 01:02:35.385
Oh, you look
lovely.

01:02:35.385 --> 01:02:38.122
Hmm.

01:02:42.326 --> 01:02:43.493
(keypad beeping)

01:02:45.495 --> 01:02:46.997
Leshing, come quick.

01:02:46.997 --> 01:02:48.232
(phone beeps off)

01:02:51.836 --> 01:02:54.071
(hip-hop music playing)

01:02:55.873 --> 01:02:57.707
So did you grow up
in River Depths?

01:02:57.707 --> 01:02:58.742
Tell me about it.

01:02:58.742 --> 01:03:00.177
Is there a river?

01:03:00.177 --> 01:03:01.711
River Heights.
Oh!

01:03:01.711 --> 01:03:03.013
Uh, yeah,
there's a river.

01:03:03.013 --> 01:03:04.314
Oh, oh, I knew that.

01:03:04.314 --> 01:03:06.450
I totally knew that.
How did I know that?

01:03:06.450 --> 01:03:08.285
(laughs)

01:03:08.285 --> 01:03:10.654
Oh, hey, hey.

01:03:10.654 --> 01:03:11.989
Oh, you want
to dance, right?

01:03:15.559 --> 01:03:16.693
(gasps)

01:03:16.693 --> 01:03:18.929
Hi.

01:03:18.929 --> 01:03:21.065
Um, I just wanted to ask you

01:03:21.065 --> 01:03:22.867
if you knew about
the secret passageway.

01:03:22.867 --> 01:03:25.069
I think you got your answer.

01:03:26.904 --> 01:03:28.906
Are you Z?

01:03:28.906 --> 01:03:31.175
Miss Drew...

01:03:31.175 --> 01:03:35.179
I suggest you rejoin your guests
and enjoy the party.

01:03:42.419 --> 01:03:44.321
(pop music playing)

01:03:49.426 --> 01:03:50.560
Hello.

01:03:50.560 --> 01:03:53.463
MAN: I warned you, drop
this Draycott business.

01:03:53.463 --> 01:03:54.564
Who is this?

01:03:54.564 --> 01:03:55.866
(dial tone)

01:03:55.866 --> 01:03:57.467
(phone beeps off)

01:03:57.467 --> 01:03:59.803
(phone ringing)

01:03:59.803 --> 01:04:01.838
Please, stop calling here.

01:04:01.838 --> 01:04:03.340
CARSON:
Nancy?

01:04:03.340 --> 01:04:04.875
Oh. Hi, Dad.

01:04:04.875 --> 01:04:06.410
Where are you?

01:04:06.410 --> 01:04:08.946
I'm going to be even later
to your party than I said.

01:04:08.946 --> 01:04:09.947
I'm sorry, honey.

01:04:09.947 --> 01:04:10.948
Is everything all right?

01:04:10.948 --> 01:04:12.416
Sounds a little crazy there.

01:04:12.416 --> 01:04:14.818
Yeah, everything's
totally mellow.

01:04:14.818 --> 01:04:15.819
Are you sure?

01:04:15.819 --> 01:04:17.087
Absolutely.

01:04:17.087 --> 01:04:18.488
Hurry home.

01:04:18.488 --> 01:04:19.489
(phone beeps off)

01:04:30.734 --> 01:04:32.636
Happy birthday, Nancy.

01:04:34.004 --> 01:04:35.239
BOY:
Back off, man!

01:04:35.239 --> 01:04:36.606
Hey!

01:04:36.606 --> 01:04:38.308
(crowd gasping)

01:04:43.513 --> 01:04:45.382
(crowd cheering)

01:04:48.618 --> 01:04:51.088
Somebody call 911!

01:04:51.088 --> 01:04:52.422
You! You know CPR.

01:04:52.422 --> 01:04:54.124
Come on, do something!
Trish is choking!

01:04:55.225 --> 01:04:56.460
This is not a joke!

01:04:58.395 --> 01:05:00.064
Out of the way,
out of the way.

01:05:00.064 --> 01:05:01.865
Coming through.

01:05:01.865 --> 01:05:03.100
Oh, my God, do
something, do something.

01:05:03.100 --> 01:05:04.734
Somebody call 911!

01:05:04.734 --> 01:05:06.136
They'll be here in 10 minutes.

01:05:08.405 --> 01:05:10.074
Does she have
any food allergies?

01:05:10.074 --> 01:05:12.109
Uh, she is insanely
allergic to peanuts,

01:05:12.109 --> 01:05:13.210
but she didn't eat anything.

01:05:13.210 --> 01:05:14.811
I had a peanut butter cookie,

01:05:14.811 --> 01:05:16.580
and we were making out.

01:05:16.580 --> 01:05:18.182
Oh, my God.

01:05:18.182 --> 01:05:20.484
I need a knife
and a ballpoint pen.

01:05:20.484 --> 01:05:21.986
Huh?
Here.

01:05:21.986 --> 01:05:23.420
Here you go.

01:05:23.420 --> 01:05:25.189
I'd like to remind everybody
that unless you've had

01:05:25.189 --> 01:05:26.556
advanced emergency
medical training,

01:05:26.556 --> 01:05:29.093
you must never
attempt this on your own.

01:05:32.029 --> 01:05:34.264
(crowd gasping, murmuring)

01:05:38.135 --> 01:05:39.136
(crowd gasping,
groaning)

01:05:39.136 --> 01:05:40.570
Holy crap.

01:05:44.874 --> 01:05:46.310
(siren blaring)

01:05:46.310 --> 01:05:47.777
You know, I have to admit,

01:05:47.777 --> 01:05:50.447
I thought you were some insane
freak idiot person before,

01:05:50.447 --> 01:05:52.949
but you're not.

01:05:52.949 --> 01:05:54.384
You're pretty terrific.

01:05:54.384 --> 01:05:56.820
Anyone can learn emergency
medical procedures.

01:05:56.820 --> 01:05:59.456
I'm talking about
how great the party was.

01:05:59.456 --> 01:06:01.725
I mean, saving Trish's life
was fantastic also.

01:06:01.725 --> 01:06:04.428
Anyways, I'd like to take you

01:06:04.428 --> 01:06:06.530
and your little friend Ned
out shopping.

01:06:06.530 --> 01:06:08.698
You really do need
a decent outfit.

01:06:12.969 --> 01:06:15.239
What happened?

01:06:15.239 --> 01:06:16.506
It was a lively party.

01:06:16.506 --> 01:06:18.775
Almost everyone
had a good time.

01:06:18.775 --> 01:06:19.976
I take it you're
Nancy's father.

01:06:19.976 --> 01:06:21.378
That's right.

01:06:21.378 --> 01:06:24.048
We responded to a
complaint from a neighbor.

01:06:24.048 --> 01:06:25.149
Dad, this is
Sergeant Billings.

01:06:25.149 --> 01:06:26.316
No, no, no.

01:06:26.316 --> 01:06:28.952
Let me say something.

01:06:28.952 --> 01:06:30.220
You had a wild party.

01:06:30.220 --> 01:06:33.690
You blew it out
when Dad was MIA,

01:06:33.690 --> 01:06:36.993
damage was done,
things went amuck, I get it.

01:06:39.063 --> 01:06:41.931
Congratulations.

01:06:41.931 --> 01:06:43.967
Getting rowdy is
part of being a normal,

01:06:43.967 --> 01:06:46.036
non-sleuthing teenager!

01:06:46.036 --> 01:06:47.271
(laughs)

01:06:49.139 --> 01:06:51.575
All right, that's a first.

01:06:54.578 --> 01:06:57.247
(laughs)

01:06:57.247 --> 01:07:00.050
* All I need is the beat *

01:07:00.050 --> 01:07:02.086
* To keep this party live *

01:07:02.086 --> 01:07:04.588
* All I need is the beat *

01:07:04.588 --> 01:07:06.856
* To keep it jumping, yeah *

01:07:06.856 --> 01:07:09.159
Hi. Obviously,
someone here

01:07:09.159 --> 01:07:10.727
needs a little help
with their look.

01:07:10.727 --> 01:07:12.796
Oh, it's not that bad.

01:07:12.796 --> 01:07:15.199
Oh, please,
it's a fashion teardown.

01:07:15.199 --> 01:07:16.600
You have some nice pieces,

01:07:16.600 --> 01:07:19.369
they're just not really
working together.

01:07:19.369 --> 01:07:21.071
Me?

01:07:21.071 --> 01:07:22.806
I was talking about her.

01:07:22.806 --> 01:07:25.575
Oh, sorry.

01:07:25.575 --> 01:07:26.410
Wow!

01:07:26.410 --> 01:07:27.844
Where did you get that dress?

01:07:27.844 --> 01:07:29.213
(gasps)

01:07:29.213 --> 01:07:31.115
Um, I made it,

01:07:31.115 --> 01:07:33.350
from one of my
mother's patterns.

01:07:33.350 --> 01:07:34.184
Oh!

01:07:34.184 --> 01:07:36.120
It is just darling.

01:07:36.120 --> 01:07:37.154
I love the sincerity.

01:07:37.154 --> 01:07:39.356
I have to take your picture.

01:07:39.356 --> 01:07:40.890
INGA:
Uh, you know what?

01:07:40.890 --> 01:07:44.561
I just remembered how much
I really hate this store.

01:07:44.561 --> 01:07:46.630
Excuse me?

01:07:46.630 --> 01:07:47.931
(weak laugh)

01:07:47.931 --> 01:07:50.800
I wish you could
stay longer.

01:07:50.800 --> 01:07:53.237
My mom said if I stayed
past the weekend

01:07:53.237 --> 01:07:55.004
that she'd turn my
room into a den.

01:07:55.004 --> 01:07:56.373
Really?

01:07:56.373 --> 01:07:58.842
Anyway, Nancy,
I just want you to know

01:07:58.842 --> 01:08:01.145
that I'm not interested
in that Inga person.

01:08:02.045 --> 01:08:04.548
In fact, she scares me.

01:08:05.515 --> 01:08:08.552
And that if you like
this Porky guy...

01:08:08.552 --> 01:08:09.419
Corky.

01:08:09.419 --> 01:08:11.921
...it's all right with me.

01:08:11.921 --> 01:08:13.990
Ned, he's 12.

01:08:13.990 --> 01:08:17.060
You just seem to really like
having him around.

01:08:17.060 --> 01:08:19.929
Ned, can I ask you a question?

01:08:19.929 --> 01:08:21.198
Mm-hmm.

01:08:21.198 --> 01:08:22.732
Can you tell
when a girl looks at you

01:08:22.732 --> 01:08:24.401
and is thinking how much
she likes you and wondering

01:08:24.401 --> 01:08:25.702
if you like her but thinking
how important it is

01:08:25.702 --> 01:08:27.237
for you to say
how you feel before she says

01:08:27.237 --> 01:08:28.572
anything more about
how she feels about you

01:08:28.572 --> 01:08:30.207
or anyone else
that you might be jealous of,

01:08:30.207 --> 01:08:32.341
because she's already saying
how she feels in her own way?

01:08:32.341 --> 01:08:35.479
Can you repeat the question?

01:08:37.180 --> 01:08:39.883
Your cab's here.

01:08:39.883 --> 01:08:42.852
Sorry to see you go, Ned.

01:08:42.852 --> 01:08:45.488
I'll, uh, see you soon.

01:08:50.794 --> 01:08:52.529
Bye, Ned.

01:09:02.138 --> 01:09:05.341
* *

01:09:12.316 --> 01:09:13.517
(melodic beeps)

01:09:15.319 --> 01:09:17.554
(knocking)

01:09:23.960 --> 01:09:25.729
Jane, are you
all right?

01:09:25.729 --> 01:09:27.029
No.

01:09:27.029 --> 01:09:29.698
Child Protective Services,
they, um, they took her.

01:09:29.698 --> 01:09:30.567
They took Allie.

01:09:30.567 --> 01:09:32.801
They said I was
an unfit parent,

01:09:32.801 --> 01:09:33.970
but it isn't true.

01:09:33.970 --> 01:09:36.139
I didn't do any of the things
that they said.

01:09:36.139 --> 01:09:38.341
Come in, come in.

01:09:42.511 --> 01:09:44.314
You're always able
to help people.

01:09:44.314 --> 01:09:46.015
Well, I can certainly try.

01:09:46.015 --> 01:09:47.984
Why don't you come downtown
with me tomorrow morning.

01:09:47.984 --> 01:09:49.018
I will.

01:09:49.018 --> 01:09:50.086
Thank you. Thank you so much.

01:09:50.086 --> 01:09:51.755
CARSON:
Sure.

01:09:51.755 --> 01:09:53.557
What's the connection?

01:09:53.557 --> 01:09:54.791
How did you two meet?

01:09:57.427 --> 01:10:01.265
I'm... Dehlia Draycott's
daughter.

01:10:02.065 --> 01:10:04.334
You're what? Wait...

01:10:04.334 --> 01:10:06.370
Dad, it's so late.

01:10:06.370 --> 01:10:08.472
Jane's tired and so am I.

01:10:08.472 --> 01:10:10.206
Let's go over all this
in the morning,

01:10:10.206 --> 01:10:11.641
in the promising light
of a new day.

01:10:11.641 --> 01:10:13.377
Right.
Have you been sleuthing?

01:10:13.377 --> 01:10:15.712
Dad, do you really think
I've been sleuthing?

01:10:15.712 --> 01:10:17.113
That's not answering
my question.

01:10:17.113 --> 01:10:18.582
You're not answering mine.

01:10:18.582 --> 01:10:20.016
Your what?
What?

01:10:20.016 --> 01:10:21.150
What?
What?

01:10:21.150 --> 01:10:22.952
(groans):
I'm going to bed.

01:10:22.952 --> 01:10:25.021
(sighs)

01:10:25.021 --> 01:10:26.790
Good night.

01:10:29.092 --> 01:10:31.928
Listen, I have
to tell you something.

01:10:31.928 --> 01:10:33.497
Right after
you first found me,

01:10:33.497 --> 01:10:36.032
someone came
to my apartment-- a man.

01:10:36.032 --> 01:10:37.801
He said if I ever
tried to prove

01:10:37.801 --> 01:10:39.703
that I was Dehlia's daughter
that I would regret it.

01:10:39.703 --> 01:10:41.971
That's why I was afraid
to talk to you that time.

01:10:41.971 --> 01:10:44.341
What did he look like?

01:10:44.341 --> 01:10:47.176
He was big...

01:10:47.176 --> 01:10:51.147
um... dark hair...

01:10:51.147 --> 01:10:52.349
scary.

01:10:54.217 --> 01:10:55.519
And he had one

01:10:55.519 --> 01:10:58.888
pale blue eye
and one very, very dark.

01:11:04.193 --> 01:11:06.396
(crickets chirping, owl hooting)

01:11:11.100 --> 01:11:13.303
(ominous theme playing)

01:11:18.875 --> 01:11:20.610
Someone has filed
grievances against you,

01:11:20.610 --> 01:11:22.346
but I don't
know who yet.

01:11:22.346 --> 01:11:25.214
But it isn't true;
none of it happened.

01:11:25.214 --> 01:11:27.951
How can they just take a kid
away from its mother?

01:11:27.951 --> 01:11:28.785
I believe you.

01:11:28.785 --> 01:11:30.253
And I think a
judge will, too.

01:11:30.253 --> 01:11:31.721
It just takes time.

01:11:31.721 --> 01:11:34.391
We'll get her back,
I promise you.

01:11:34.391 --> 01:11:36.760
Now... is
there anyone

01:11:36.760 --> 01:11:38.928
who might have
something against you?

01:11:38.928 --> 01:11:42.866
Dad, look, there's something
I need to tell you.

01:11:42.866 --> 01:11:44.434
It has to do with
this whole...

01:11:44.434 --> 01:11:46.336
(church bells ringing)
Carson!

01:11:46.336 --> 01:11:48.405
Nancy.

01:11:48.405 --> 01:11:49.639
After Jane's little revelation,
I found out

01:11:49.639 --> 01:11:51.107
who the lawyer
for the estate was,

01:11:51.107 --> 01:11:52.576
and I gave
him a call.

01:11:52.576 --> 01:11:55.044
He and I are going to talk over
something privately.

01:11:55.044 --> 01:11:56.145
Do you have your car?

01:11:56.145 --> 01:11:57.914
Down the block.

01:11:57.914 --> 01:11:58.948
What are you two, um...?

01:11:58.948 --> 01:12:00.384
Dinner, tonight.

01:12:00.384 --> 01:12:01.685
I've got a lot of questions,

01:12:01.685 --> 01:12:04.588
and I think you just
might have the answers.

01:12:07.391 --> 01:12:09.292
(sighs)

01:12:09.292 --> 01:12:11.561
Feel like some hot cocoa?

01:12:13.363 --> 01:12:15.565
(TV playing softly)

01:12:17.967 --> 01:12:20.169
ANNOUNCER: ...Channel presents
the life and death

01:12:20.169 --> 01:12:21.571
of Dehlia Draycott.

01:12:21.571 --> 01:12:23.139
JANE: It's so weird--
I never used to think

01:12:23.139 --> 01:12:25.709
about her at all, and now
it's like I see her everywhere.

01:12:25.709 --> 01:12:28.077
(reporters clamoring,
cameras clicking)

01:12:28.077 --> 01:12:30.514
(thunder rumbling)

01:12:30.514 --> 01:12:33.383
What if I am
an unfit mother?

01:12:33.383 --> 01:12:34.618
I mean, I don't know
what I'm doing.

01:12:34.618 --> 01:12:35.885
No one ever taught me
what to do.

01:12:35.885 --> 01:12:36.820
Jane...

01:12:36.820 --> 01:12:38.354
Nancy, I don't think
you understand

01:12:38.354 --> 01:12:40.390
what it's like growing up
without a mom.

01:12:41.290 --> 01:12:44.594
Actually, my mother died
when I was very young.

01:12:44.594 --> 01:12:47.363
Oh, God, I'm sorry.

01:12:47.363 --> 01:12:49.132
I didn't know.

01:12:49.132 --> 01:12:52.636
You've been so nice to me.

01:12:54.471 --> 01:12:57.073
Sometimes, I-I think
I can remember her,

01:12:57.073 --> 01:12:59.676
but I never know
if what I'm remembering

01:12:59.676 --> 01:13:02.412
is something I saw
in a picture...

01:13:02.412 --> 01:13:04.548
or is just made up.

01:13:05.381 --> 01:13:07.250
She's, um...

01:13:07.250 --> 01:13:10.487
she's a mystery.

01:13:14.491 --> 01:13:17.627
DEHLIA (on TV): Someone in
the village told me that

01:13:17.627 --> 01:13:19.663
the will is in
the Chinese box.

01:13:24.601 --> 01:13:26.636
Wait a minute.

01:13:35.311 --> 01:13:36.946
What are we looking for?

01:13:36.946 --> 01:13:38.815
A clue.

01:13:38.815 --> 01:13:41.284
DEHLIA (on TV):
It's empty.

01:13:41.284 --> 01:13:43.019
You must make the dragon bow.

01:13:46.523 --> 01:13:48.191
(lever squeaking)

01:13:55.098 --> 01:13:56.232
The will.

01:13:56.232 --> 01:13:58.201
I must have fallen asleep
and heard this dialog.

01:13:58.201 --> 01:13:59.636
I finally found it.

01:13:59.636 --> 01:14:01.971
Dehlia used a clue from
one of her own movies

01:14:01.971 --> 01:14:03.707
to show someone
where to find the will.

01:14:03.707 --> 01:14:05.909
Now all I have to do
is make the dragon bow.

01:14:05.909 --> 01:14:08.211
Okay, you lost me at "dragon."

01:14:08.211 --> 01:14:10.547
I'll be back later!

01:14:12.348 --> 01:14:14.283
Hello?

01:14:14.283 --> 01:14:15.785
Hello, Mr. Louis?

01:14:15.785 --> 01:14:19.055
Are you in there?

01:14:19.055 --> 01:14:20.724
Hello?

01:14:22.559 --> 01:14:23.960
I'm sorry to
interrupt your dinner,

01:14:23.960 --> 01:14:26.229
but this means so much
to two of my friends.

01:14:26.229 --> 01:14:28.231
It's fine.

01:14:32.201 --> 01:14:34.804
(squeaking)

01:14:38.908 --> 01:14:40.877
It's the will.

01:14:42.712 --> 01:14:46.049
If you want it,
you can have it.

01:14:48.084 --> 01:14:49.485
Thank you so much.

01:14:50.887 --> 01:14:54.223
"I give all my property
and assets to my daughter,

01:14:54.223 --> 01:14:57.226
born July 28, 1981."

01:14:57.226 --> 01:14:59.262
I knew it.

01:14:59.262 --> 01:15:00.263
(sirens blaring in distance)

01:15:03.733 --> 01:15:05.501
(auto-dial beeping)

01:15:05.501 --> 01:15:06.536
(line ringing)

01:15:06.536 --> 01:15:07.571
Dad.
CARSON: Hi, honey.

01:15:07.571 --> 01:15:08.772
I have to talk to you.

01:15:08.772 --> 01:15:10.106
What number are
you calling from?

01:15:10.106 --> 01:15:12.275
My cell phone--
the one you gave me.

01:15:12.275 --> 01:15:13.743
I didn't give you a cell phone.

01:15:13.743 --> 01:15:15.945
(beeping quietly)

01:15:20.216 --> 01:15:22.552
CARSON:
Honey...?

01:15:22.552 --> 01:15:24.320
Dad, I have to get off
this phone.

01:15:24.320 --> 01:15:25.421
Everything's fine.

01:15:25.421 --> 01:15:26.422
I'll see you tonight.
Nancy...

01:15:26.422 --> 01:15:27.891
(tires screech, phone beeps off)

01:15:28.892 --> 01:15:30.694
(gasps)

01:15:30.694 --> 01:15:32.929
(muffled screams)

01:15:34.798 --> 01:15:36.532
(engine revving,
tires screeching)

01:15:47.410 --> 01:15:49.613
* *

01:15:59.355 --> 01:16:01.557
(light clattering)

01:16:12.168 --> 01:16:14.203
* *

01:16:23.546 --> 01:16:26.349
* *

01:16:37.260 --> 01:16:40.529
* *

01:16:40.529 --> 01:16:43.800
(whispering): So they're the
ones who've been breaking in.

01:16:47.170 --> 01:16:49.172
* *

01:16:57.113 --> 01:17:00.784
(snoring)

01:17:05.454 --> 01:17:07.791
(television playing softly)

01:17:08.624 --> 01:17:09.993
(board creaks quietly)

01:17:14.964 --> 01:17:16.666
MAN (on TV):
They've got to stop.

01:17:16.666 --> 01:17:18.768
It's not your fault.

01:17:21.037 --> 01:17:23.106
WOMAN (on TV): You do
believe me, don't you?

01:17:23.106 --> 01:17:24.974
(creaking)

01:17:31.080 --> 01:17:33.416
(creaking)

01:17:44.794 --> 01:17:46.896
* *

01:17:57.506 --> 01:18:00.176
* *

01:18:05.681 --> 01:18:07.416
(loud thump)

01:18:07.416 --> 01:18:09.452
Go check on her.

01:18:09.452 --> 01:18:11.454
Wait, I want
to see this part.

01:18:11.454 --> 01:18:14.457
Kids will love it just
for making chocolate pasta.

01:18:25.534 --> 01:18:28.104
* *

01:18:54.798 --> 01:18:56.099
(sighs)

01:19:06.575 --> 01:19:08.044
(loud thump)

01:19:16.886 --> 01:19:19.455
* *

01:19:27.330 --> 01:19:29.065
* *

01:19:34.770 --> 01:19:36.305
She's not there.

01:19:36.305 --> 01:19:38.741
Look again.

01:19:38.741 --> 01:19:40.409
She's not there.

01:19:44.413 --> 01:19:46.115
(creaking)

01:19:47.016 --> 01:19:48.584
(clattering)

01:19:48.584 --> 01:19:50.453
Excuse me.
Hey!

01:19:51.988 --> 01:19:54.390
Go get her!

01:20:03.632 --> 01:20:05.434
Hey!

01:20:09.438 --> 01:20:10.874
Hey!

01:20:10.874 --> 01:20:13.042
(truck engine accelerating)

01:20:13.042 --> 01:20:15.378
She's getting away! Jump!

01:20:15.378 --> 01:20:18.381
I don't...
Go! Go get the car!

01:20:18.381 --> 01:20:20.149
Idiots!

01:20:29.458 --> 01:20:31.027
(engine revving)

01:20:39.969 --> 01:20:42.271
(tires screeching)

01:20:51.280 --> 01:20:52.315
(gasps)

01:20:54.483 --> 01:20:56.019
(car horns blaring)

01:20:56.019 --> 01:20:57.220
(screams)

01:21:00.856 --> 01:21:04.560
(tires screeching)

01:21:04.560 --> 01:21:05.929
(Nancy grunts)

01:21:08.197 --> 01:21:10.833
(SUV speeding off
into distance)

01:21:10.833 --> 01:21:12.468
NURSE:
Right there.

01:21:12.468 --> 01:21:15.738
(phones ringing,
people conversing)

01:21:15.738 --> 01:21:16.705
Hi, Dad.

01:21:16.705 --> 01:21:17.706
Are you okay?

01:21:17.706 --> 01:21:19.042
What happened?

01:21:19.042 --> 01:21:21.877
Just your run-of-the-mill
car accident.

01:21:21.877 --> 01:21:23.612
I swerved out
of control

01:21:23.612 --> 01:21:26.149
because, um...

01:21:26.149 --> 01:21:28.251
because men were chasing me.

01:21:28.251 --> 01:21:30.119
I've been working on a case.

01:21:30.119 --> 01:21:31.754
Uh, I'm going to
give you two some time.

01:21:31.754 --> 01:21:33.923
Thank you.

01:21:33.923 --> 01:21:35.858
I started to tell you today.

01:21:35.858 --> 01:21:37.560
You could have been killed.

01:21:37.560 --> 01:21:38.627
Do you realize that?

01:21:38.627 --> 01:21:40.930
I was just trying
to do the right thing.

01:21:40.930 --> 01:21:43.299
This is a very dangerous city.

01:21:43.299 --> 01:21:45.901
The world is not like
River Heights.

01:21:45.901 --> 01:21:47.170
I know.

01:21:47.170 --> 01:21:49.138
I mean, I tried to be normal.

01:21:49.138 --> 01:21:50.806
I really tried.

01:21:50.806 --> 01:21:54.343
I just start working on
something and... I can't stop.

01:21:54.343 --> 01:21:56.980
Wonder where you got that from.

01:21:58.614 --> 01:22:02.318
I mean, the idea of a girl
out there without her mom...

01:22:02.318 --> 01:22:05.054
Dehlia wanted
to leave Jane

01:22:05.054 --> 01:22:07.290
the estate,
and I found the will.

01:22:07.290 --> 01:22:10.359
Like you always
say, others first.

01:22:10.359 --> 01:22:13.029
I just wish you had talked
to me about this.

01:22:13.029 --> 01:22:14.697
It'll be okay, Dad.

01:22:14.697 --> 01:22:16.399
We'll work it out.

01:22:16.399 --> 01:22:17.433
You're my guy.

01:22:17.433 --> 01:22:19.035
(scoffs)

01:22:19.035 --> 01:22:20.836
(knocking)
Hey, kiddo.

